title: company potatoes
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until onions are clear (do not brown).
Mix all ingredients and put into buttered or Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Casserole is done when potatoes are tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and asparagus pasta toss
directions: Cook pasta until almost tender.
Add asparagus; continue to cook 3 to 4 minutes more.
Drain well.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef, onions and garlic over medium heat until beef is no longer pink (8 to 10 minutes).
Drain off fat.
Combine pasta mixture with beef mixture; toss well.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: basic scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
With pastry blender or two knives, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Beat buttermilk and eggs in small bowl. Pour onto dry ingredients and stir with fork until mixture comes together.
On lightly floured surface knead dough 5 or 6 times. Transfer to prepared cookie sheet.
With floured hands pat into an 8 inch circle.
Cut into 8 wedges with a long, sharp, floured knife.
(Do not separate.)
Bake 14 to 16 minutes until golden. Transfer to wire rack.
Serve warm.
Makes 8.

title: date loaf
directions: Cook milk, sugar and chopped dates until it forms a soft ball in cold water, stirring a few times while cooking to prevent burning.
Let it set a few minutes, then add vanilla and beat until cool.
Add pecans and continue to beat until very stiff. Pour onto a clean damp cloth and form a long roll.
Let it stand until cold.
Cut into slices of desired thickness with a sharp knife.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add 4 egg yolks (beaten) and mix well.
Add chocolate mixture to creamed mixture.
Sift and measure flour. Sift again with soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in 4 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Gently fold in nuts and coconut.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes or until done.

title: baked cream of chicken
directions: Put chicken in deep cooking dish such as Corning Ware.
Season chicken.
Add soup and cover.
Cook on low temperature until done and tender.

title: meaty macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Brown beef, onion and celery in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in sauce, salt and pepper.
Combine meat mixture with macaroni and pour in 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook Wesson oil, onion and pepper until onion is done.
Add other ingredients and simmer for about 15 or 20 minutes.
Pour in bottles and store in refrigerator; use as needed.

title: polish barley soup
directions: Simmer pearl barley in 1 1/2 c. of stock until tender.
Add butter or oil gradually.
Boil chopped vegetables until tender in the remainder of the stock, then add the cooked barley and seasoning.
Add sour cream when ready to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crunchy popcorn mix
directions: Toss, in large bowl, cereal, corn, soybeans and raisins. Makes approximately 7 1/2 cups.
Great diet snack.

title: sour cream cookies(large recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and form into roll.
Freeze and cut into slices.
Bake.

title: hawaiian dinner
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Sprinkle spicy topping on batter.
Bake in an 8-inch square pan 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: In large heavy
skillet, over medium heat, saute ground beef, stirring occasionally, until red color disappears.
Pour off fat. Add onion, green pepper, garlic, crushed red pepper, chili powder,
cumin,
oregano
and
salt;
mix
well.
Cook, stirring, until onion and green pepper are tender.
Add beans, tomatoes, corn and tomato sauce; stir to mix well, breaking up tomatoes with
fork.
Simmer
slowly,
covered
and
stirring occasionally, until
thickened
and flavors are blended, about 45 minutes.

title: onion sandwiches
directions: Chop onion fine.
Combine with water, sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Let cool overnight.
Drain the onions the next day. Use white bread, trimming off brown edges.
Spread mayonnaise and powdered sugar on bread, then onions (about 1 teaspoon per sandwich).
Put together and cut into finger sandwiches.
(Can be frozen and thawed to use later.)

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dress shrimp.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Season to taste.
Add eggs, celery and lettuce.
Season.
Mix gently.
Add onion and desired amount of mayonnaise.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour or cornstarch and salt. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir the mixture until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Separate eggs; set whites aside for meringue, if desired.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Gradually stir 1 cup of hot mixture into yolks.
Bring to a gentle boil for 2 minutes more. Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.

title: mrs. erdman's chewies
directions: Mix peanut butter, corn syrup and sugar into a large pot. Bring to a full boil; then beat to mix well.
Add cornflakes and mix until cereal is well coated.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and cool.

title: three layer dessert
directions: Place pineapple in long Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar over pineapple, then spread pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple and pie filling mixture.
Slice margarine over entire mixture and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Delicious served hot with ice cream.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Add milk to slightly beaten egg yolks, then combine flour mixture and milk mixture. Cook in top of double boiler until the thickness of custard.
Add vanilla.
Line baking dish with wafers.
Slice bananas over wafers.
Pour 1/2 custard over bananas and wafers.
Repeat process again.
Beat egg whites with 6 tablespoons sugar.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour on top of pudding.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes, or until top is slightly browned.

title: taco pie
directions: Place biscuits in 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger and then add taco seasoning mix (follow taco seasoning directions). Let simmer.
Place meat over biscuits.
Add some shredded cheese. Place in oven at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.
When done, take out of oven and, in order, add sour cream (spread over on top of meat and biscuits), lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and onions (optional).
Cut into squares and serve.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Remove from heat; add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla, mixing well after each addition. Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes at 325°. Easily doubled.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, butter and sugar together.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Mix in flour, then add flavoring.
(You can also add 1 package of dry Dream Whip, if desired.)
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat
together	at
high speed for 10 minutes the eggs, sugar, oil,
juice and vanilla.
Blend in the dry ingredients (which have been sifted together) a little at a time.
Fold in the nuts. Put
of
the
batter in well-greased Bundt pan which has been dusted with sugar instead of flour.
Arrange 1 cup of sliced apples on top;
sprinkle with 1 1/2 teaspoons of sugar
and
1/2 teaspoon
cinnamon.
Add another third of the batter, the
rest of the apples, sugar and cinnamon as before. Cover with
the remaining
third of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or less if it tests done.
Sprinkle with 1 1/3 cups powdered sugar and 5 tablespoons lemon juice.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet. Drain. Melt butter in skillet on medium heat. Saute onions and peppers. Add remaining ingredients except rice. Let simmer 10 minutes. Add rice, salt and pepper to taste. Mix well. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: chicken (turkey) tetrazzini
directions: Blend soup, water and undrained mushrooms.
Cook spaghetti. In casserole, put it all in and top with crumbs or I top with shredded cheese.
May use any kind of cheese or a combination of cheeses.

title: apple muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine apple and next 3 ingredients and stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Divide batter evenly among 12 muffin cups sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 28 minutes or until a wooden pick comes out clean.
Remove from pans immediately.
Let cool on a wire rack.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes, mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake in 11 x 12-inch pan at 350° until light brown on top, 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add tomato sauce, lemon juice, salt and grated onion.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into ring mold or individual molds.

title: noodle kugle
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar and extracts until light in color and frothy.
Add sour cream, cottage cheese and milk.
Beat lightly until blended.
Add noodles.
Stir until blended.
Pour into buttered baking dish (9 x 13-inch).

title: doubly good yeast rolls
directions: Combine 1 teaspoon sugar, salt, yeast, 1/2 cup water and eggs; mix 2 minutes on low speed.
Set aside.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 cups water and shortening in a large mixing bowl.
Mix for 3 minutes (I mix by hand).
Add yeast mixture; mix 3 minutes at medium speed.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 3 hours or until doubled.
Punch down; cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out as needed.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Dough may be refrigerated for up to 4 days.

title: taco salad
directions: Break up lettuce into small pieces.
Place in large bowl.
Add cheese, onions, chili beans and tomato.
Before serving, add crushed Fritos or Doritos and Catalina dressing.

title: baked acorn or butternut squash
directions: Wash squash; halve and clean out seeds.
Rub oil all over squash.
Put in a shallow baking dish and add water to halfway of squash.
Sprinkle a small amount of brown sugar over squash. Cover baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: broccoli casserole 1
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; mix all ingredients and put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with more stuffing crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in oleo until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano.
Add beef. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Place half of the spaghetti in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half of the vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese.
Repeat layers. Mix the soup and water until smooth; pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 12 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Into mixing bowl, blend peanut butter, powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 tub of Cool Whip.
Blend with mixer at low speed. Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
For best results freeze 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: golden wassail
directions: Place the cinnamon and cardamom in cheesecloth.
In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Add the cinnamon and cardamom. Bring to a boil.
Reduce and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Float slices of fruit and sticks in bowl.
Makes 18 (4 ounce) servings.
(Good for people who don't like apple juice.)

title: seafood strata
directions: Crumble bread in baking dish.
Place sauteed vegetables on top,
then the tuna and layer of cheese.
Mix milk, beaten eggs, thyme
and salt.
Pour over top with Parmesan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Measure sugar, salt and oil into big bowl.
I also add to dry ingredients a little onion salt and a little garlic powder to give added flavor.
Mix all together.
Let rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Grease cookie sheets. Spread dough and top with favorite toppings and bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tortilla chicken
directions: Wrap chicken in foil and steam in oven until tender, about 1 hour.
Bone and cut chicken into large pieces.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch squares.
Combine soups, milk or broth, chili salsa and onion.
Butter flat baking dish, place layer of tortillas, a layer of chicken and a layer of sauce.
Repeat.
Top with cheese. Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Flavor with taco sauce, if desired.

title: chicken diable
directions: Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Stir in other ingredients.
Roll chicken in butter mixture to coat on both sides.
Arrange in a single layer in same pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for about 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice to which you have added mushrooms and sliced water chestnuts.

title: taco tossed salad
directions: Cook and stir ground beef until brown; drain. Stir in taco sauce and heat. Toss lettuce, green pepper, tomato, olives, cheese and chips.
Spread beef mixture and salad dressing over the lettuce mixture.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: spice 'n crumb banana bars
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass).
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large mixer bowl, combine first 4 ingredients; mix at low speed until crumbly.
Press 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumb mixture for topping.
To remaining crumb mixture, add remaining ingredients; beat 1 minute at medium speed until well blended.
Spread over crumb crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes. While hot, spread 1 pint marshmallow cream on cake.
Cool.

title: cheeseburger skillet dinner
directions: Prepare the macaroni and cheese per directions on box.
Brown ground beef in skillet with onions and drain.
Mix in vegetables, catsup, water, mustard; cook until vegetables are crisp and tender, 10 minutes or so.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Mix in macaroni.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Boil pasta according to directions.
Add frozen vegetables and cook 2 minutes more.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Add cream sauce and toss well.

title: caramel dip
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Add Karo, brown sugar, Eagle Brand and vanilla.
Cook until smooth.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Cover onions, cucumbers and peppers with ice and wait until melted.
Combine sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Drain water and pour on vinegar mixture.
Wait 3 days.
Will keep in refrigerator 6 months.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together well.
Add next five ingredients and mix again.
Add oats, raisins and nuts (if desired) and blend with a spoon.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
The size of cookies depends on you.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water (suit individual).

title: white-chocolate-chunk macadamia cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease two 17 x 14-inch cookie sheets.
In large bowl of electric mixer, beat butter, sugars, egg and vanilla at medium-high speed unti fluffy.
Reduce mixer speed to low; add flour.
Increase mixer speed gradually and beat just until blended.
Stir in nuts and chocolate.
Drop heaping tablespoonfuls dough 2 1/2-inches apart onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 1 sheet at a time 17 minutes or until edges of cookies are lightly browned and tops look dry.
Cool on sheet on wire rack 5 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool completely.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix together flour and salt; dissolve yeast in warm water. Mix all together and knead.
Cover and let rise in warm place for about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Line pizza pan.
Top with favorite toppings.
Bake in hot oven (500°) for 10 minutes.

title: sun-dried tomato pesto
directions: In a food processor, chop garlic and nuts; set aside.
Blend marjoram, parsley, basil, butter and olive oil.
Puree 20 sun-dried tomatoes.
Chop 5 sun-dried tomatoes.
Add all ingredients together, including grated Parmesan cheese.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels in milk in double boiler.
Combine all other ingredients except chocolate chips and nuts.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving a portion of mixture for top.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on baked crust; pour on caramel mixture.
Add remaining crumbs and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until brown. Makes 24 bars.
Yield:
15 bars.

title: refrigerator cherry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baked pie shells. Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend shrimp a few at a time in the blender.
Empty from blender and do a few more until all are done.
Mix in cheese, mayonnaise and Pet milk; add to shrimp and mix well.
Salt to taste.
Lemon juice, onion and garlic may be added.

title: fudge pecan pie(everyone's favorite!)
directions: Roll out pie crust; put in bottom of pie tin.
Break crackers coarsely into pie shell.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan; boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot generously with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: sweet irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar together.
Add caraway seed and raisins.
Stir in buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Knead dough on a lightly floured board for about 1 minute, then shape it into a round loaf and put it into an 8-inch greased round pan.
Pat flour lightly over the top surface, then cut crosswise into the top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or until done.
Bread should have a hollow sound when tapped.
Makes 8 servings.
(For heart patients.)

title: chicken and pepper cheese sauce
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon of the flour, salt and ground peppers; toss with chicken to coat.
In 10-inch skillet, cook chicken pieces in hot oil 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove chicken; add onion, sweet pepper, jalapeno pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender. Stir in remaining flour.
Add broth, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Stir 1 cup of hot mixture into sour cream; return to skillet.
Add chicken; heat through (do not boil).
Serve on linguine.

title: potato sausage patties
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Shape into patties and fry in a skillet.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls(golabki)
directions: Cut core out of cabbage.
Put cabbage into a large kettle of boiling water over high heat.
With tongs, remove leaves as they wilt, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Let leaves stand until cool enough to handle.
Carefully cut out thick center vein from each leaf. Cool remaining cabbage and cut coarsely or chop and put on bottom and top of cabbage rolls.
Saute onion in oil.
Parboil cabbage as per directions.
Mix chuck, pork, rice, onion, salt and pepper well.
Fill each leaf of cabbage with meat mixture and roll. Secure, you can use a toothpick in each one.
Line bottom of large pot with some cut up cabbage and place cabbage rolls on top.
Mix 2 cans of tomato soup with 1 can of water and pour over rolls. Top with remaining chopped cabbage.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: no-bake peanut logs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Shape into logs with hands, about 2 inches long.
Chill for one hour or more.
Prepare chocolate glaze.
Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Melt paraffin wax in a separate pan, then add to chocolate.
Using tongs, dip logs into warm coating mixture.
Place on wax paper to dry and cool.

title: lemon and lime supreme salad
directions: Whip cream.
Add marshmallows.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Dissolve jello in 3 cups boiling water, then add the pineapple juice.
Let set until partially set in refrigerator, then gently fold pineapple, cottage cheese and marshmallows into jello.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 6 people.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cornflakes and 1/4 cup butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Mix cornflakes and 1/4 cup butter.
Place on casserole last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soup, eggs and cheese and pour over drained broccoli. Put fine bread crumbs on top and pour melted butter over crumbs. Add 1/2 cup chopped onions, if desired. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; stir in oats.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and set aside while you make the filling.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Cut chicken breasts in cubes and add to onion and green pepper.
Cook on medium for 5 to 7 minutes; stir often.
Put all of this into a greased casserole.
Mix Cheez Whiz, sour cream, cream of chicken and taco seasoning.
Stir well until well blended.
Put over chicken.
Crush tortilla chips and top chicken.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: tuna cheeses
directions: Mix tuna, celery, cheese, onion, salt, pepper and mayonnaise. Spread buns with margarine; fill buns with tuna mixture.
Place each sandwich on a piece of aluminum foil and fold edges securely. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° until hot, about 20 minutes.
Makes 24 sandwiches.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: In a mixing bowl or food processor, combine the flour, oats and salt.
Slowly drizzle in the oil with the motor running (or with a fork if mixing by hand).
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons ice water, a few drops at a time, until mixture begins to form a ball.
Pat the dough into a 9-inch pie plate (or roll between two sheets of wax paper; remove top sheet and turn pastry into pie plate, then remove second sheet of wax paper).
Form a rim and flute the edges.
For an unbaked pie shell, fill and bake according to recipe.
For baked pie shell, prick the pastry with a fork in several places.
Bake in a 400° oven until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 starch/bread and 2 fat.
Calories:

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix beans and corn together.
Place in bottom of large casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together (except crackers and butter).
Pour mixture on top of corn and beans. Melt butter; mix crumbled crackers in butter and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hawaiian bread dip
directions: Prepare Hawaiian bread.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into bread.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yum! Eat with bread or chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain and stir in chicken soup, butter and salt.
Break up cheese and add to mixture. Crumble Ritz crackers and add.
Pour into baking dish and crumble some Ritz crackers over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump into cake pan in layers in order given:
cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple and cake mix.
Dot oleo over cake mix and add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to pkg. directions. Mix next 4 ingredients. Layer broccoli and mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350 degrees. Add 1 pkg. Ritz cracker crumbs; top with pats of butter. Bake 10 more minutes or until brown.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Heat applesauce.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Add lime jello (do not add water).
Cool the mixture.
Add coconut, pineapple chunks, salt and ginger ale.
Chill until firm.

title: potluck corn pudding
directions: Brush a 3-quart shallow dish or pan generously with some of the melted butter.
In mixing bowl, combine cornbread mix, corn kernels, cream-style corn, sour cream and butter; mix with spoon until well blended.
Pour into pan.
Place on center shelf of oven; bake at 350° until top is golden and crusty and knife comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove; let cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients; add to shortening mixture.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook until mixture bubbles over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch morsels together over very low heat or over hot but not boiling water, stirring until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Spread evenly over Rice Krispies mixture.
Cool until firm; cut.

title: no cholesterol deviled eggs
directions: Cook egg substitute until done, being careful not to brown. Put in blender.
Add salt, pepper, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Blend well.
Set aside.
Peel eggs.
Cut in halves and discard yolks. Fill egg whites with egg substitute and sprinkle with paprika.

title: breakfast sweet rolls
directions: Let bread thaw overnight in refrigerator.
Two to 2 1/2 hours before serving, cut bread into 18 pieces and roll into balls. Grease a 9-inch round cake pan.
Combine cinnamon and sugar in bowl or Baggie and cover rolls with mixture.
Place in pan and pour remaining sugar and cinnamon over rolls.
Drizzle melted butter over top and let rise, covered with wax paper.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Mix and simmer.
May add rum or whiskey.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Rinse chicken in cold water. Place in large pot with bay leaf over medium heat, covering chicken with water. Cook until the chicken falls apart. Remove from heat. Remove chicken from bone and chop. Remove bay leaf. Add water to pot. Add onion and 1 teaspoon salt. Sprinkle with black pepper. When chicken starts boiling, slowly place tortilla squares until done.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and let marinate for at least 3 hours. Add a little more olive oil and vinegar, if desired before serving. Add Parmesan cheese and serve. Serves 2.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add hash browns, onion and green pepper.
Cook until potatoes begin to brown.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Spread potato mixture in pan. Top with ham.
Pour eggs over all ingredients; season with salt and pepper.
Gently stir to coat all ingredients with egg. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.

title: corn bread
directions: Pour into greased pan.
Bake until done at 350° to 400°.

title: caramel pie
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, sugar, flour, cornmeal, egg yolks, milk and margarine.
Cook until thick.
This takes about 25 to 30 minutes to boil down.
Stir frequently.
Pour filling into baked pie shell.
It's great with a meringue made of the 3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread over pie and place under broiler until lightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saute onions and seasoning in butter until tender. Add cream of mushroom soup, wine and all other ingredients, except crawfish tails. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Test for taste and add more seasoning to desired taste. Add crawfish tails. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Pour into partially baked pie shell. Cover top of pie with another pie shell. Brush with garlic butter. Bake until brown and bubbly in oven heated to 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Combine all ingredients.
The frozen broccoli should be thawed and drained.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamy maple frosting
directions: Mix margarine or shortening, salt, syrup, vanilla and 1 cup confectioners sugar. Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: In a bowl, cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Cream.
In second bowl, mix together all dry ingredients. Add to butter mixture and set aside.

title: pot luck spuds
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together in an 9x13 inch pan. Drizzle the margarine over the top. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour. (You may use cream of mushroom soup instead of cream of chicken.)

title: caramel corn
directions: In 2 quart casserole, combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on high 3-4 minutes, stirring every minute until comes to a boil.
Microwave 2 minutes more.
Then stir in baking soda, vanilla and nuts.
Place popped corn in a large brown paper bag.
Pour syrup over popped corn.
Stir well.
Microwave on high 1 minute.
Shake well.
Microwave on high 1 more minute.
Pour into container and stir to separate.
Store in air tight container.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine water, sherry, onion, curry and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken pieces; simmer for 1 hour.

title: trifle
directions: Cut the cake in pieces, 1 x 3-inches.
Split pieces of cake in two and put strawberry preserves between.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Peel broccoli stems and quarter.
Cut off fat from bacon and then cut strips lengthwise every 1/2 to 1 inch.
Cook until crisp. Drain.

title: easy nacho dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, picante sauce and onion together.
Spread over shallow pan.
Top with tomato and cheese.
Serve with nachos.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Pare cucumbers and slice as thin as possible.
Put in a salad bowl with onion.
Sprinkle with salt, add sour cream and stir well to	coat
all slices.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Serves 4.

title: puppy chow mix
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and butter. Mix in a plastic bag the Rice Chex and peanuts.
Pour chocolate mix on top and shake real well. Then pour in confectioners sugar. Shake well. Pour in bowl. Serve to your pups (kids).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add mayonnaise and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Chill overnight.

title: cajun pork ribs
directions: Thaw well in refrigerator 1 1/2 to 2 days before use.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together to make 1-inch balls.
Brown on cookie sheet in oven, about 1/2 hour.
In crock-pot, add 1 large jar of Prego spaghetti sauce and 1 can crushed tomatoes, enough to cover meatballs.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Enjoy.

title: lane cake
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy and gradually add 1/2 cup sugar. Beat until soft peaks form.
Cream 1 1/2 cups sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat well after each.
Fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Pour into 4 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.
Then remove from pans and cool completely.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes and onions in a 3-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle salt, pepper and flour over potatoes and toss to coat evenly.
Dot butter around the dish and pour milk over top. Cover and microwave 20 to 25 minutes until potatoes are tender. Stir and rotate once during cooking.
Allow to stand for 5 minutes after cooking.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Combine yeast, sugar, salt and 1 1/2 cups flour in large mixing bowl.
Stir
to mix.
Add milk, water, butter and egg. Beat until well blended.
Add remaining flour to make stiff batter.
Spoon into greased muffin cups filling each about 2/3 full.
Cover.
Allow to rise about 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Put all ingredients
in
top of double boiler.	Cook in double boiler over
medium
heat until caramels are melted and mixture is	 smooth,
stirring
constantly.
Store	in
glass canning jars (makes five
ounce
jars); does not need to be pressure sealed. Will
store
on
shelf
for
several months. Each jar makes 4 servings.
Heat
to
serve (I use the microwave).
It's great over ice cream.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Melt oleo in electric skillet.
Place chicken pieces in pan. Mix catsup and Coke together and pour over chicken pieces.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add drained spinach and cook until warm.
Add sauteed mushrooms and sour cream, combined with mushroom soup.
Fold into spinach-hamburger mixture and cook until warm. Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and slightly brown.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice until all water is dissolved.
Mix eggs, sugar and milk.
Pour the mixture into rice and when it comes to a boil, add 1 teaspoon vanilla and mix.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Ready to serve hot or cold.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Spread cream cheese over bottom of plate or favorite dish. Spread well drained crabmeat over cream cheese.
Pour generous portion of seafood cocktail sauce over crabmeat.
Serve with favorite crackers.
Enjoy!

title: potatoes alberta
directions: Mix ingredients in frying pan.
Cover and allow to simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat until smooth; drizzle over warm cake.
Serves 12.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix well and pour in muffin pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add corn, corn meal mix and sour cream.
Put in baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Top with cheese as soon as done.

title: mostaccioli casserole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients.
Mix in spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
Add oregano, basil and a little brown sugar, if desired. Blend the cheeses together.
Cook noodles until tender.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix sugar, pumpkin, oil and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients and add together with sugar ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: sweet and sour mustard sauce
directions: Mix and stand overnight the Coleman's mustard and vinegar. Next day, beat in eggs and salt.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool and add 1 1/2 cups of mayonnaise.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all of the ingredients into mixing bowl.
Beat about 3 minutes. Form into balls (about 24).
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Boil water and drop in marshmallows.
Melt Jell-O; add sour cream to mixture.
Stir well.
Add pineapple and nuts.

title: los angeles "bicycle shop cafe" garlic chicken
directions: Marinate garlic a few minutes with additional 3 ounces peanut oil.
Put salt and pepper generously on inside and outside of chicken.
With basting brush, apply chopped garlic on inside and outside of chicken.
Heat butter and oil in thick, large pan.
Put in chicken and golden brown it on every side.
Put in the oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn chicken around and baste every 15 minutes.
Once cooked, remove chicken from pan, throw fat away and unglue the juices from the pan with a wooden spoon.
Add about 6 ounces of water.
Boil for 3 minutes or so, to reduce to the right consistency.
Strain juices.
Cut chicken in half and pour the sauce on top.

title: dutch chocolate pudding cake
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over top (do not stir).
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes. Spoon sauce from bottom of pan over top.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add peas, onion, mushroom soup, milk, cheese and butter.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Beat in remaining ingredients except coconut. Stir in coconut.
Bake in 9-inch unbaked pie shell 40 minutes at 350°.
Center will be soft.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake triangles
directions: Combine crumbs, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press firmly into bottom of a foil-lined 8-inch square baking pan.
In blender combine cheese, milk, 1/2 cup sugar, egg, flour and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Melt chocolate bits in saucepan; cool slightly.
Stir in 3/4 cup batter; mix.
Pour remaining batter into pan.
Pour chocolate mixture over batter; swirl with knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Chill 1 hour.
Remove from pan; cut into triangles.
Top with Raspberry Sauce.
Serves 8.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time. Then add flour and vanilla.
Pour batter into a jelly roll pan. With a knife, score batter into 24 squares.
Place 1 tablespoon of pie filling into center of each square.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 20 minutes).
Cut again into squares.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix by spoon.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp cheese broil
directions: Decrust bread slices.
Cut each slice into 4 pieces.
Place shrimp on top of bread.
Spread mixture of Hellmann's, Parmesan and onion on top.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Broil until golden brown.

title: irish coffee
directions: In chilled bowl, beat cream, confectioners sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Refrigerate.

title: beef-pork goulash
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Melt butter in large, heavy kettle.
Add onion; cook slightly, stirring often, until wilted. Season meat with salt and paprika.
Add to onion and cook, uncovered, stirring often, for 25 minutes or until onion and meat form a liquid.
Add water.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.
If desired, thicken liquid with flour mixed with a little cold water and simmer a few minutes longer.
Top with the sour cream; sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with noodles and a bowl of sour cream.

title: whoopie pies(moon pies)
directions: Add the first 3 ingredients to the next 5 ingredients well, then add hot water and cocoa and mix well.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine the first 7 listed ingredients and pour into ice cream freezer.
Fill to mark with milk.
Pack in ice and salt.
Freeze.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a large casserole dish with Pam. Place chopped cabbage in dish. Brown ground beef. Add bell pepper and onion.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cheese. Pour over chopped cabbage.
Bake 1 hour.
Add cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Put drained asparagus in buttered baking dish.
Chop eggs and put layer over asparagus, then layer of cream cheese and layer of peas. Dot with butter and season with salt and pepper.
Mix milk and soup together and pour over vegetables.

title: beefy mexican soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and green pepper in Dutch oven until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, chili powder, garlic salt, salt and tomatoes with liquid.
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling; stir constantly and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer.
Stir occasionally.
After 10 minutes, stir in macaroni, corn with liquid and olives.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Garnish with corn chips, if desired.
Makes about 9 cups.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain apricots; add water to juice to make 2 cups.
Dissolve jello in the cup of hot water and mix.
Add juice.
Mash apricots and blend with cream cheese, using electric mixer.
Add all ingredients and congeal.

title: kase kneple(mock cheese buttons)
directions: Cook noodles per package directions; drain.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream, half and half, salt and pepper and part of the onions.
Alternate this mixture with noodles in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle croutons on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Just before it is finished baking, add the remaining green onions.

title: thousand island salad
directions: Toss the first 5 ingredients together.
Combine remaining ingredients and add, tossing to blend.

title: darn good chocolate cake
directions: Place a rack in the center of the oven and preheat the oven to 350°, mist a 12 cup bundt pan with vegetable oil spray and then dust with flour, shake out the excess flour.
Set pan aside.
Place the cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, warm water and oil in a mixing bowl. Blend with an electric mixer at slow speed for 1 minute.

Stop the mixer and scrape down the sides of the bowl with a rubber spatula. Increase the speed to medium and beat 2 to 3 more minutes. Add the 4 eggs and then mix an additional 2 minutes, scraping the sides of the bowl as needed.
Then fold in your chocolate chips.
Make sure they are dispersed throughout the batter.
Pour the batter into the bundt pan and place into the oven.

Bake cake until it springs back when pressed with your finger and it pulls away from the sides (usually 45 to 50 minutes). Cool cake for approximately 20 minutes. Run a long knife around the edge of the cake, invert it onto a cooling rack and allow it to continue to cool for approx. 20 minutes.
It is good when served warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: sopaipillas
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Gradually add water, stirring with a fork. The dough will be crumbly. On a lightly floured surface, knead the dough for 3 minutes or until smooth.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes. Roll out into a 12 x 10 inch rectangle.
Cut into 12 squares. In a deep-fat fryer, heat 2 inches of oil to 375 degrees. Fry sopaipillas (dough squares) for 1 to 2 minutes per side.
Drain on paper towels. Keep hot in warm oven. Serve with honey or dust with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in loaf pan.
Spread ketchup on top of loaf.
Add water to pan.
Cook until 150° or 160° is reached. If cooked in microwave, cover with plastic wrap.
Turn pan around once during cooking.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Mix butter and peanut butter; stir in sugars and mix well. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour mixture until combined. Drop dough from a teaspoon on baking pan; flatten with a fork. Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: cream chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, paprika, salt, pepper, thyme and dill in paper bag.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time; shake until chicken is well coated with flour mixture.
Heat butter in large frying pan.
Add chicken and brown on all sides. Remove from pan.
Add onions to pan; saute until lightly browned. Add pimento.
Stir in remainder of seasoned flour until well blended.
Add cream or evaporated milk, stirring well; stir in bouillon and lemon juice.
Place chicken in casserole dish; pour sauce on top.
Cover and bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove; serve hot.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a bowl, mix together milk, cream cheese and vanilla extract.
Blend until lumps disappear.
Mix for 2 minutes.
In an 8 x 9-inch pan, combine butter and graham crackers and press firmly into sides and bottom.
Add mixture.
Chill for 1 hour. Serve.
Dip bottom of pan in warm water.

title: mam-maw's tea cakes
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and beat well until thoroughly mixed.
Add baking powder, water, vanilla and a pinch of salt.
Add enough flour to roll out easily on a floured board.
Cut into desired shapes and bake in a moderate 350° oven until done.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook, then blanch the noodles.
Shred or crumble corned beef. Mix all together and put in a 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake one hour at 350° or longer if needed to. Should be bubbly and hot through.
Serves 20.

title: snowflake pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add salt and lemon juice. Chill until it is slightly thickened.
Then place in bowl of ice and water and beat with rotary eggbeater until fluffy and thick. Fold in 1/3 of the whipped cream and 1/2 cup coconut.
Put into a graham cracker crust.
Spread the remaining whipped cream over this and sprinkle the rest of the coconut on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: beef jerky
directions: This is enough marinade for approximately 3 pounds of flank steak.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix white and brown sugar with shortening.
Add eggs.
Add 1 cup flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and soda.
Beat in rest of flour and oatmeal.
May add chocolate chips, raisins or dates. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple pie cobbler
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt.
Mix with apples and beat slightly.
Pour into pie crusts.
Dot with margarine and add top crust.
Cut slits into top crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: fantastic mushrooms
directions: Wipe the mushrooms with a damp cloth and cut the stem ends. Cream together the butter, parsley, onion, mustard, salt, cayenne, nutmeg, and flour in food processor or mixer.
Place mushrooms in a 1-quart casserole dish.

title: avocado cherry tomatoes
directions: Cut
thin
slice
from	top
of cherry tomatoes. With a small-sized
melon	ball
cutter,
scoop
out
seeds and pulp; discard.
Sprinkle	inside	of tomato shells lightly with salt and sugar.
Invert
shells
on paper towels and drain 30 minutes. Combine pureed avocados with remaining ingredients; mix well. Fill
tomato
shells with avocado mixture using a small knife or piping bag.
Arrange tomatoes on serving dish.
Serve chilled. Serves 6.

title: effie's cabbage and sausage
directions: Peel potatoes and cube or cut up.
Brown potatoes and onion in 2 tablespoons of oil.
In separate boiler, cut up cabbage and cook in a small amount of water.
Slice sausage and add to potatoes and onion mixture.
After cabbage is tender, add to sausage, potatoes and onion.
Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes over low heat.
Serve with cornbread and enjoy.

title: strawberry soda
directions: In a covered blender container, with blender at high speed, blend milk and strawberries 15 seconds; pour into five 12 ounce glasses.
Add scoop of ice cream to each glass; slowly add soft drink to fill glasses about to top.
Makes five 1 1/2 cup servings.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Overlap biscuits in 8-inch or 9-inch cake pan in a spiral fashion.
Combine butter, sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Spread over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and green pepper in oil until beef has lost its pink color and is crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole; cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil the macaroni until tender. Drain well. Mix the macaroni, tuna, peas, Parmesan cheese and the margarine together. You may want to add more Parmesan cheese and margarine.
Serves 10 people.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
In an other bowl, beat the eggs and add the milk and vanilla.
Add milk mixture to flour and sugar slowly until mixed well.
Add coconut and then melted butter.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 400° until crust begins to brown, about 12 minutes.
Turn oven back to 350° for about 20 minutes until custard has browned on top.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare
potatoes.
Cut	 in
quarters.	Combine
flour, cheese, salt
and
pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes in water and shake a
few
at a time in bag, coating well.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Place potatoes in a layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once.
When golden brown, sprinkle with parsley. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spice-molasses cookies(good in winter)
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add egg and molasses; mix well.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Combine dry ingredients with milk and 2 of the 6 eggs.
Add onion and turn into greased large pan or skillet (mixture is crumbly).
Bake at 450° until done, not brown.
Remove from pan; crumble into another big pan; add remaining 4 eggs and not broth. Season to taste with approximately 3 teaspoons sage and 2 teaspoons celery seed.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Steam for 3 hours.
Serve with hard sauce.
Pudding may be reheated.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Trim
fat
from
pork chops.
Grease large skillet with fat. Cook
chops
in
skillet over medium heat until brown on both sides.
Drain
off
fat.
Sprinkle chops with salt.
Top each chop
with
onion slice.
Stir together in a bowl orange juice, brown
sugar,
allspice,
lemon juice and water.
Pour orange juice
mixture
into skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Arrange the sweet potatoes (drained) and orange slices on the pork chops.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar and syrup. Add beaten eggs, nuts and vanilla. Pour into unbaked crust and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: eggless cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift flour.
Measure and sift with baking powder, soda and spices.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour into well oiled loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cream cake
directions: Beat cream lightly, not stiff.
Beat eggs well, add sugar and beat again.
Fold cream into egg mixture.
Sift flour 3 times and add gradually to mixture.
Add flavoring.
Bake in angel cake tin at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: preposterous pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown on top or knife inserted comes out clean.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix everything together really good.
Let set overnight for seasonings to blend.
Good to dip any vegetable in.

title: freezer homemade bread
directions: Place 3 cups flour, salt, sugar and yeast in bowl.
Heat water to 120° to 130°.
Add oil and pour over dry ingredients; mix well. Stir in 1 cup additional flour; turn onto floured surface and knead in an additional cup of flour.
Separate into 2 loaves. Grease loaves, then place on greased cookie sheet and immediately place in freezer.
After frozen, wrap individually and return to freezer.

title: cheesy buffalo wings
directions: Melt margarine.
Dip drumstick part of chicken wing into margarine.
Using food processor, make coarse meal out of cheese nips and coat wings.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: angel mousse
directions: Put chocolate morsels in double boiler over boiling water. Stir until melted.
Separate eggs and whip whites stiff and yolks slightly.
Take chocolate mixture off stove and add yolks of eggs, beaten and return to double boiler for 5 minutes.
Take off the stove; fold in small amounts of whipped cream and egg whites until well blended.
Break 1/2 of angel cake in bite-size pieces; place in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour chocolate mixture over all. Chill several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate and cut in 9 pieces.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix fancy Chinese vegetables to long grain and wild rice and seasoning packet and drained water chestnuts.
Mix mushroom soup and 1 can of water.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until cooked.
Peel and rinse.
Cut into quarters or smaller if preferred.
Place in casserole dish.

title: pam's sauce
directions: Crush plum tomatoes in blender or food processor and place in large pot.
Add 3/4 of a can of water for each can of tomatoes, oil and sprinkle enough garlic powder to cover the tops of the tomatoes lightly.
Give a small shake of red pepper.
Cover; simmer on high while you fry the meats.
Stir occasionally.
Fry meats with bones first.
Add to sauce as they are browned.
Fry sausages next and lastly, meatballs.
Add to the pot.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and cook for 30 minutes.

title: catzy's french dressing
directions: Mix all very well.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut on bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon caraway seed.
Layer corned beef and caraway seed.
Drizzle with Thousand Island dressing.
Layer tomato slices next.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: aunt nona's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in oil and salt and pepper.
Add garlic, tomato paste, water and red pepper.
Cook very slowly for a couple of hours or longer.

title: corn flakes candy
directions: Heat the sugar and corn syrup only long enough to melt sugar. Add the peanut butter (or coconut).
Stir in the corn flakes, a cup at a time, and mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper or foil.
Munch away!

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt butter in 13
x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick, salt and dash of pepper.
Coat chicken with mix.
Place in pan with melted butter.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until nearly done.
Drain and toss with butter. Brown beef, onions and green pepper.

title: bran muffins
directions: In small bowl, pour water over raisins; add soda and cool.
In very large bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add flour (reserve 1/2 cup flour if using nuts), salt and cereal.
In another large bowl, beat eggs; add buttermilk and fold in raisin mixture.
Add all at once to flour mixture; mix until well moistened.
Add nuts, floured with reserve flour.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Bake when needed in muffin tins at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beer muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium size muffin cups or use paper baking cups.
Mix all ingredients; beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 can cranberry sauce.
Cool until syrupy.
Fold in sour cream and pecans.
Place in mold or 8 x 8-inch container.
Chill until firm.

title: fettuccine
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese in heavy pot.
When cheese is almost melted, in bits, add cream.
Remove from heat as soon as cream has heated thoroughly.
Cook fettuccine using salt and oil. Drain.
Toss with sauce, toss again with Parmesan cheese, sprinkle with pepper and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine filling ingredients in large bowl.
Stir until combined. Spoon into graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Yields 1 large or 2 smaller ones.

title: batter bread
directions: Bake in hot oven quickly.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 3 quart saucepan.
Cook to a soft ball stage (240 degrees on a candy thermometer) stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper. Yield 3 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries and add 1 cup cold water.
Cook until tender. Add sugar and cook for 5 minutes.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water and dissolve into hot cranberries.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Add nuts and celery and mix thoroughly.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly. Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting. Blend flour and salt; stir in. Mix in nuts. Chill. Heat oven to 400°. Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar. Cool. Roll over in sugar again. Makes about 4 dozen 1-inch cookies.

title: joann's microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Place popcorn and nuts in a large, microwave-safe bowl.
Set aside.
Place brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in 2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring each minute, until boiling.
Microwave 2 minutes more.
Remove from oven and add baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and nuts.
Stir well and quickly.
Return to microwave and cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir well.
Spread in a large roasting pan.
Cool and break apart.
Yum, yum!

title: pineapple-orange punch
directions: Mix Crystal Light and water; add pineapple juice and chill. Add ginger ale or Sprite when ready to serve.

title: raw apple icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at low speed of mixer until apple is finely chopped.
Increase speed to high as icing thickens and beat until icing is thick and smooth, about 5 minutes.
Spread on cake.
This icing is best served the same day it is made.
Yields sufficient icing for two (8-inch) layers or 1 (13 x 9 1/2-inch) sheet cake.

title: tuna fritters
directions: Mix biscuit mix with wheat germ.
Add beaten egg with milk. Fold in tuna.
Drop by teaspoon into hot shallow fat.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel or rack.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add cake mix.
Reduce eggs to 2.
Reduce oil to 1/3 cup.
Mix 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 38 minutes.
May be frosted to serve as cake.

title: pecan spread
directions: Drop dried beef into a small pan of boiling water; remove from stove and drain well in a strainer.
Run it under cold water and chop finely (this removes excess salt from beef).
Mix cream cheese, milk, pepper, onions and garlic powder together and blend well.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream and mix.
Toast pecans with butter. Pour cream mixture into a small baking dish; sprinkle pecans on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with Melba toast.

title: apple-cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Combine cheese, apples, flour, lemon juice and rind, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and egg yolks in a large bowl.
Mix well until blended.
Add raisins.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into cheese mixture.

title: cinnamon cupcakes
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese-broccoli soup(make in crock-pot)
directions: Place melted butter and onion in crock-pot. Gradually add flour to pot, stirring constantly with a whisk or spoon. Add chicken broth and stir until smooth. Add salt, celery, carrot and broccoli. Stir to combine. Cover and cook at low for 6 to 7 hours or at high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: hungarian doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: candied apples
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Place
all
ingredients
in a saucepan
and
cook, stirring occasionally, until butter melts and sugar
is dissolved.
Pour the mixture into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking
dish.
Bake for 40 minutes or until apples are tender and sauce is bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tomato tortellini soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil in a large saucepan.
Add tortellini and cook for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes longer.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bones and layer in square dish.
Cut 1 stick of margarine over layered chicken.
Mix soup with a little water; pour over chicken.
Take biscuits; split or pull apart in halves.
Lay biscuits on top of soup mixture. Bake in oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Insert a toothpick to test for doneness.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Combine oil in melted chocolate.
Beat eggs and add sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled chocolate mixture.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Roll into large balls and roll in 4x sugar (confectioners) and bake 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: oriental rice
directions: Cook together sausage, onions and pepper.
Scramble eggs. Cook rice separately.
Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Add peanuts.
Cook until the water is cooked out of them.
Add vanilla to taste.
Spread peanuts out on cookie sheet and bake in 300° oven for 15 minutes on each side.

title: marshmallow fudge candy
directions: Cook sugar, cream, syrup, cocoa and marshmallows to a soft-ball stage. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Cool. Add walnuts and beat until thick. Pour into buttered dish.

title: braunschweiger party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Serve with crackers.

title: heath bars
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam or line with foil.
Line with saltine crackers.
Boil 1/2 cup margarine and 1/2 cup brown sugar for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers and spread evenly and fast. Bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Cover with 1/2 to 1 pound chocolate chips.
Return to oven for 1 minute.
Spread and cover with chopped nuts.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugars creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg whites and water.
Stir in pecans.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and bake 30 minutes at 250°.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pie imperial
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Stir in milk. Cook over hot heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir at least half of hot mixture into eggs. Then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate pieces and stir until melted.
Stir in flavorings.
Cook to lukewarm, stirring occasionally.
Blend sour cream into chocolate mixture.

title: icebox cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in the water; cool.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; add jello. Fold whipped Carnation into jello mix.
Add pineapple and blend.

title: muddys prune cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs.
Then add prunes, then flour with other dry ingredients added to flour and milk.
Cook in two pans at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Ice with confectioners sugar icing.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cream potatoes with hot milk. Mix in rest of ingredients except last 2. Put in a buttered 2-quart casserole. Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° until heated through, approximately 30 minutes.

title: salad relish
directions: *May leave off salt, if you wish, because vegetables may have had some in each can.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Cook 3 hours in crock-pot on low or 1 hour on high or in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: light bread
directions: Heat milk, Crisco and sugar until Crisco melts.
Remove and cool to a lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in approximately 1/4 cup warm water.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Two to four days before serving:
In a large bowl, make marinade.
Combine the first 10 ingredients.
Put meat in marinade and place in refrigerator, covered, 2 to 4 days, turning meat each day.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In mixer bowl, combine 1 quart cold chicken stock and all ingredients.
Add to remaining simmering chicken stock.
Simmer until thick.
To serve, in bottom of each bowl, put chopped avocados, chopped, cooked chicken, crisp corn tortilla chips and grated Cheddar cheese.
Pour hot soup over topping.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in shallow 2-quart microwave-safe dish.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add broth until blended. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 4 to 4 1/2 minutes until thickened.
Stir once.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Gently stir in potatoes and onion to coat.
Cover with lid and microwave 16 to 18 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn twice until potatoes in center are tender.
Let stand 10 minutes to complete cooking.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and sugar together in a bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture looks like cornmeal.
Add buttermilk and sourdough starter.
Add flour until forms a soft dough.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead gently, about 1 minute.
Roll out into 1/4 to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Let rise in a warm place for 1/2 hour. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until brown.
Brush with butter before baking.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine all the ingredients above, except the pastry shell, and blend thoroughly.
Pour the mixture into pastry shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from the edge of the filling comes out clean. Cool the pie.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg.
Blend all dry ingredients; stir into shortening mixture.
Roll dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: goulash
directions: Cook hamburger meat; season with salt, pepper, garlic salt and meat tenderizer.
Add all ingredients; simmer for 1 hour.
Tastes good as leftovers, too!

title: easy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Melt butter in an 8 x 8 pan. Sprinkle the graham crackers, coconut and chips in layers over the butter. Finally, drizzle the condensed milk over all. Bake 45 minutes. Cool and cut into small bars.

title: savory shrimp stir-fry
directions: Toss shrimp into salt and pepper mixture to coat.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet.
Add shrimp and stir over high heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Add garlic and green onions to skillet and stir over medium heat 1 minute.
Add pea pods, vegetables and chicken broth to pan and stir over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Return shrimp to pan and cook, stirring, 1 to 2 minutes.
Season to taste and garnish with your favorite fresh herb.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: country ham
directions: Soak ham overnight; wash ham and place in roaster in 5 cups water with skin side up.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Put roaster in oven, then turn oven up to 500° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven off. Leave ham in oven for 3 hours.
Turn oven on again to 500° for 15 minutes only.
Turn oven off.
Leave ham in oven for 6 to 8 hours. Do not open oven door once you have started cooking.
Let ham cool before slicing.

title: dressing (german style) for turkey or pork roast
directions: Wet the bread after it has been cubed into bite sized pieces. Let sit in water and soak for about 1/2 hour.
Chop up the onions and stalks of celery.
Squeeze the water out of the bread; add all of the other ingredients.
Mix by hand until all ingredients are well blended.
You can stuff the turkey with the dressing or bake it in a separate dish.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry ground beef and season with onions, ortega diced chilies, salt and pepper.
Chop salad, dice tomatoes, add olives, hot sauce and mix together.
Add beans, cheese and avocado.
Toss with dressing.
Add chips, ground beef and top with sliced avocado.

title: snow ball cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine-shortening.
Mix in water and vanilla.
Then flour and nuts.
Roll dough into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool (do not brown cookie).
Dip in powdered sugar.

title: diet dessert
directions: Heat pineapple and jello.
Cool.
Mix in other ingredients. Pour into glass dish and refrigerate.

title: imitation crab salad
directions: Mix together chopped crab and cabbage slaw; add salt. Mix in coleslaw dressing and mayonnaise.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Chop onion and green pepper and saute in hot olive oil.
Use a large nonstick frying pan or electric skillet.
Add tomatoes, cut up in small pieces.
Saute until tomatoes form a sauce (if planning a main dish, add ground beef here).
Add rice and saute for a few minutes until well coated.
Stir frequently.

title: pork chop teriyaki
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Place pork chops in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Cover.
Marinate 3 to 6 hours or overnight in refrigerator, turning chops occasionally.
Broil in oven or on grill about 15 to 20 minutes on each side or until done, brushing occasionally with remaining marinade.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Premeasure and set aside oatmeal and peanut butter.
Put margarine, sugar, cream and cocoa in a skillet on medium-high heat.
Stir as margarine melts to mix ingredients well.
Stir constantly until mix comes to a boil.
When a rolling boil, cook for 1 1/2 minutes exactly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla flavoring, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: easy linguini and clam sauce
directions: Begin cooking pasta according to directions on package.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add mushroom soup and undrained can of clams as well as basil, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: pecan divinity
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in saucepan over low heat. Stir until sugar dissolves. Cook without stirring to 252° (hard-ball stage). Remove from heat and pour in a fine stream into 2 stiffly beaten egg whites, stirring constantly. Continue beating until it holds its shape and loses gloss. Add vanilla and broken nuts. Drop quickly from tip of spoon onto waxed paper in peaks.

title: lime sweet pickles(yields 5 to 6 quarts)
directions: Let cucumbers set in lime water overnight.
Rinse 3 times in cold water.
Let stand in cold water 3 hours.
Add sugar to vinegar and spices as desired.
Drain cucumbers.
Simmer in vinegar 1 hour.

title: crabmeat pie
directions: In an uncooked 9-inch pie shell, place crabmeat and Swiss cheese.
Pour sauce over pie:
flour, eggs, cream and seasoned salt.
Cook for 45 minutes in 400° oven.

title: grandma sullivan's graham cracker pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar, butter, egg white and cinnamon in bowl. Remove 2 teaspoons of mixture and set aside. Press remaining mixture into an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: orange date-nut bread
directions: Grate or grind rind of 1 orange; squeeze juice and add water to make 1 cup.
Add to this dates (cut-up) and boil with soda until dates are softened.

title: pussy willow salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir until smooth.

title: souvenir shrimp curry
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Coat 9 x 9-inch pan with margarine.
Spread batter over bottom.
Pour 1 can sour cherries and juice (not pie filling) over batter.
Bake in 350° preheated oven about 20 minutes. Apricots, peaches or pineapple may be used.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and club soda.
Beat well. Add nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring to a boil butter and water. Mix in flour; stir until it forms a ball. Beat together eggs and gradually add to mixture. Put into greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: tea biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients over shortening.
Blend with pastry blender.
Add raisins and buttermilk; mix.
Knead until smooth. Roll out on board into log and slice with knife.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes on an ungreased pan.
Ice if desired.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Beat the eggs with sugar.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and celery.
Chop onion and place in 2 1/2-quart Dutch oven.
Boil until tender on medium heat.

title: cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine tapioca, salt, sugar, cherries and almond extract; let stand 15 minutes.
Turn into unbaked pie shell and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust, flute edges and vent top.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: beef curry on rice
directions: Saute garlic and onion in 2 tablespoons oil in skillet until tender.
Remove onion and garlic.
Combine flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt and pepper and roll meat in this mixture.
Put remaining fat in skillet.
Brown meat.
Put onion on top of meat; add bouillon cube dissolved in 1 cup boiling water and curry powder. Cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Add tomato sauce.
Reheat and serve over rice.

title: ashe orange-pineapple lite cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges with juice.
Blend all ingredients with electric mixer (oranges will break up while mixing) and pour into a very lightly greased (not floured) 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: green enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic.
Add onions and cook until soft.
Add chilies.
Add soup with 2 cans of water and let simmer.
Dip tortillas in hot butter to soften. Arrange in layers with cheese on top.
Heat until cheese is melted in 350° oven.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cut chicken into small chunks.
Mix all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Season to taste.
Serve on lettuce.
Great to take for lunch if you're counting fat grams.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in salt, flour and baking powder that has been sifted together.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Drop by teaspoonful into confectioners sugar.
Roll around and shape into a ball.
Place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake. Makes about 50 cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Combine and add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in 2 lightly greased loaf pans at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: Saut onion in oleo until tender; add milk and cubed cream cheese.
Stir until cheese has melted.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Serves 5 (1-cup servings).

title: curried spinach dip
directions: You can use fat-free ingredients.

title: brown sugar sausage
directions: Slice sausage in thin slices.
Mix brown sugar, catsup and mustard together.
Stir in sausage and place in pan.
Heat oven to 350° and bake until heated thoroughly about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Put oil and all seasonings in large pan.
Stir crackers into mix.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir after 1/2 hour.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Saute chicken 5 minutes on each side in oil.
Remove chicken; saute sliced vegetables.
Add chicken and water.
Let stream 15 minutes and add sauce.
Let cook 3 minutes and serve with rice.

title: huevos rancheros(for 2 to 3)
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain and pour off fat.
Saute onion, jalapenos and green pepper in oil.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, garlic, chili powder and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Thin as necessary with tomato juice or water.
Break eggs into sauce.
Simmer, covered until done.
Serve on warm buttered tortillas.
Top with grated cheese and bacon.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Saute onions tender in oil in skillet. Combine beans, (deviled ham) and prepared mustard.
Arrange half of the mixture in 2-quart casserole dish.
Place half of the onions and tomatoes (sliced) over the beans.
Sprinkle with half of the salt and sugar.
Repeat, using rest of ingredients.
Cover and bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes.
Easy and good!

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Chop onion and green peppers.
Saute onion and peppers in butter until soft; add flour and salmon (which has been boned). Remove from heat; stir in milk.
Place mixture in greased casserole; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: creamy deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks; mash.
Blend in cream cheese, relish and seasonings, mixing well.
Refill whites.
Yields 16 deviled eggs.

title: buttered biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add 1/2 cup milk and stir with fork, adding more milk as you go until dough is just moist enough to form a ball.
Roll out on floured board and cut into biscuits.
Brush tops with melted butter and bake in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot with butter and jelly or a milk gravy.

title: clara's jello salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O, hot water, pineapple, cranberries, banana and strawberries together.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Let stand until firm (20 or 30 minutes). Spread sour cream over top.
Pour remainder of Jell-O mixture over sour cream and let cool until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add bananas and mix well. Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until tested with toothpick.

title: pineapple bran bread
directions: Combine bran and juice.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir pineapple, eggs and shortening into bran mixture.
Add dry ingredients and nuts. Blend.

title: connie's pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk together until smooth.
Toast coconut and pecans in butter; let cool.
Pour pie crust 1/2 full with filling.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans and drizzle caramel over that.
Repeat until crust is full (2 layers).
Freeze until ready to eat.

title: lemon gem muffins with cream cheese
directions: In a bowl, whisk together flour, baking soda, salt and sugar. In another bowl, whisk together eggs, lemon juice, butter and vanilla.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture and stir batter until it is just combined.
Pour batter into buttered 1/3-cup muffin tins and bake in the upper third of a preheated 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until a tester comes out clean.
Turn muffins out onto a rack, let them cool, and serve them with the cream cheese.
Makes 24 small muffins.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix flour, butter and confectioners sugar together thoroughly.
Press into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan building up a 1/2 inch edge.
Bake 20 minutes.
