title: coconut sour cream cake(serves 18)
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.
When cool, turn out and split into two layers.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir to keep rice from settling to the bottom and bake another 1/2 hour.
Serve with chow mein noodles.

title: bran muffins
directions: Crush Bran Buds to fine crumbs. Stir together with flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine milk, egg whites and oil.
Mix well. Add
flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups coated with cooking spray. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes. Serve warm. Yields 12 muffins.

title: string pie
directions: Cook pasta according to package; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Combine spaghetti, Parmesan cheese, eggs and butter; mix well.
Place in a 13 x 9 baking pan.
Spread cottage cheese over top.
Pour sauce mixture on top.
Sprinkle Mozzarella over top.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: poached eggs
directions: Heat 1 1/2 to 2-inches of water to boiling. Reduce to simmer. Break each egg into measuring cup or saucer.
Hold each egg in/on cup/saucer, close to water's surface.
Slip 1 egg, at a time, into water. Cook until desired doneness, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove egg with slotted spatula.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 3 teaspoons of mix in a cup.
Add boiling water.

title: fruit-filled oatmeal bars(no eggs)
directions: *Need a shortcut?
Substitute a 10 ounce jar of preserves for homemade filling.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together; roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.
Ready to serve.

title: coconut rum pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, oleo and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add the flavorings. Alternately add the flour, milk and baking powder.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Pour glaze over hot cake.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs with mixer.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating mixture until thick and foamy.
Wit a spoon, stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, walnuts and currants; stir gently into zucchini mixture just until blended.
Divide the batter equally between 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until a toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; turn out on wire racks to cool thoroughly.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, salt and boiling water and let stand, covered, without stirring or boiling, while you brown the hamburger in butter, adding onions, celery, mushrooms and soy sauce.
Combine with rice.
Bake slowly, 1 hour, in covered casserole dish, 9 x 11-inch (Pyrex).
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Blend in flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in buttermilk and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until set.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips together. Put in baking dish, cover with cheese.
Top with potato chips. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in four greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans. Combine water and lemon juice, sprinkle over apples.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt; cut in butter until crumbly. Stir in cheese lightly.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until apples are tender and topping is crisp. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Yields 100 servings.

title: deluxe potatoes
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 12-inch greased Pyrex pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10 persons.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and
flour.
Next, add baking powder and vanilla.	Bake in 2 layer cake pans (reserving enough batter for a third layer)
at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool on waxed paper.
To the remaining batter, add the spices, raisins, nuts, and dates, if desired.
Bake in layer cake pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.	This third layer goes between the first 2 layers.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Brown meats separately.
Drain.
Combine with cheese and spices.
Heat slowly until cheese is melted.
Spread on slices of bread; place on cookie sheet.
Place sheet of wax paper on top; keep adding layers of bread pizzas with wax paper between.
Freeze overnight.
After frozen solid, bake one layer at a time at 400° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes (when bottom of bread feels like toast).

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Pour into a 1 1/2 gallon ice cream freezer container and fill with milk until 3/4 full.
Use freezer as directed.
Mixture usually freezes within 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese rolls
directions: Unroll 1 can of crescent rolls into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not press seams together.
Mix cream cheese with 1 cup sugar and vanilla and spread over rolls.
Place second can of rolls over top.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Then pour on mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad(ambrosia)
directions: Cut up fruit
in
large
bowl.	Pour
lemon
juice over fruit. Add 1
cup coconut.
Dissolve 1 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons cornstarch in
cup water and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and
slowly add 1 beaten egg yolk; cook until thick. Fold in 1 beaten
egg
white	and pour over fruit.
Delicious served with pound cake.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Fold in beaten egg yolks. Sift flour and soda and add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts and coconut; fold in beaten egg whites. Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Mix ingredients, adding black walnuts last.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake in conventional oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300° and bake about 30 minutes more or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Serve warm or cold.

title: blender hollandaise sauce
directions: Place all ingredients, except water, in blender.
Cover and turn machine to medium speed.
When ingredients are well mixed, remove top and, with blender running, gradually pour in boiling water.
Run until contents are thoroughly blended, about one minute.
Heat, stirring constantly over hot (but never boiling) water until the sauce is the consistency of custard.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Put layer of chicken in casserole dish.
Then add cream of celery soup (undiluted) and cream of chicken soup.
Melt oleo. Add stock and stuffing mix.
Place on top of casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: amaretto or kahlua pie
directions: Melt marshmallows with cold milk and salt over hot water. Cool until mixture will mound on spoon.
Stir in Amaretto or Kahlua.
Beat whipping cream until it holds peaks.
Fold into marshmallow mixture.
Chill 30 minutes until mixture holds ripples.
Turn into a cold cookie crust and freeze.
Put slivered almonds on top.

title: ukrainian paska(origin: ukrainian)
directions: Put milk and water in saucepan and scald.
Set aside to cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast cakes with approximately 1 tablespoon sugar and a little warm water.
When bubbly, put in large mixing bowl.
Add lukewarm milk and water.
Mix. Add flour (approximately 2 cups) until consistency of thin sour cream.
Mix well. Leave in warm place (covered) 1 to 4 hours until bubbly.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, crushed bananas and salt.
Mix soda with sour milk and add to the first mixture.
Fold in flour, add nuts and bake in loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour, or until knife inserted in middle of bread comes out clean.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake as directed.
As soon as it comes out of the oven, pour Eagle Brand milk on top.
Let it completely cool.
Put Cool Whip on top, then cover with coconut.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in boiler.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, pecans and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased pan.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until very light colored.
Add milk, then juice, blending well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 minutes.
(A 9-inch pie will need about 10 minutes less baking time.)
Cool well, then chill at least 15 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: ever so easy fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes in either 4 greased and floured loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.

title: garlic chicken with rosemary
directions: Rinse and dry chicken.
Coat the cavity with juice of 1 lemon and 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Insert the pods from one head of garlic, along with 3 sprigs of rosemary, salt and pepper; close the cavity with string.
Rub the outside of the bird with the juice of 1 lemon and the remaining olive oil.
In a heavy, deep pot, distribute the rest of the garlic and remaining rosemary.
Cover; bake at 376°.
Check it out in one hour to see if it is done.
Cook until done.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Saute onions, then add ground beef and brown until done.
Add beans, corn, salt and pepper.
Stir until warm, then add cheese and hot sauce.
This is a quick and easy meal.
Serve with cornbread.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine.
Stir in sugar. Add eggs and flavorings. Blend until smooth. Stir in cake flour.
Blend mixture until smooth.
Pour into tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: marinade(for chicken parts or steak)
directions: Marinate chicken pieces or steak for 2 to 3 days in refrigerator (no kiddin').
Cook (broil or bake) as usual.

title: rice pilaf with asparagus
directions: In 3-quart microwave proof dish, combine butter, garlic and onion. Cook on High 3 minutes. Stir in rice, coating every grain. Stir in broth. Cover tightly and cook on High 5 minutes. Stir in asparagus. Cook on Medium for 4 minutes until most liquid has been absorbed and rice is tender.
Stir in parsley. Cover; let stand 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese during last 10 minutes of baking time.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook sweet potatoes and add all ingredients, except 2 tablespoons brown sugar. Turn into casserole and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons brown sugar over top.

title: creamed chipped beef
directions: Cook dried beef in butter until edges fizzle; blend in flour slowly.
Add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add Worcestershire sauce, if desired, and a dash of pepper.

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and then gently fold in potatoes and put into baking dish.
Top with cheese; sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until thoroughly heated and browned on top.
Mixture can be made ahead and baked just before serving.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix eggs, Crisco and sugar. Add other ingredients. Mix well. Bake in preheated oven 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan.
Add sugar and milk.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil 2 minutes 15 seconds.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool.
Add peanut butter to taste, nuts if desired and beat.

title: chinese five spice pork
directions: Trim chops.
Cut in strips.
Place pork in mixing bowl. Combine all remaining ingredients and marinate for 1 hour.
Ensure pork is well coated with marinade.
Heat oil in a frying pan; add pork and marinade and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently until sauce thickens.
It will turn a rich brown color.
Serve on rice.

title: pizza cookie(makes 1 cookie)
directions: Line a 12-inch pizza pan with foil; grease foil and set aside. Cream butter and add sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour and next 3 ingredients and mix well.
Add vanilla and mix.
Stir 1/2 cup chocolate pieces and 1/4 cup pecans.
Spoon batter onto prepared pan, spreading to within 1 inch of edge.
Sprinkle with coconut and other 1/4 cup pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows and remaining 1/4 cup chocolate pieces on top.
Bake an additional 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in wedges. Makes one 12-inch cookie.

title: christmas crunch candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips over simmering water in top of double boiler.
Let cool.
Stir in salted peanuts, raisins and marshmallows.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on paper.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Cook 1st 5 ingredients until very thick.
Stir mixture into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Place in pie pan and set in refrigerator until thoroughly cold.
Add pineapple (drained) and serve with whipped cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredient well and chill before serving.

title: cheesy garlicy chicken
directions: Melt margarine with garlic powder added.
Mix bread crumbs, cheeses, salt and pepper.
Cut chicken into quarter breasts size and dip into margarine/garlic mixture, then in cheeses/bread crumbs mixture.
Place in large shallow baking pan.
Pour remainder of margarine over chicken pieces.
Refrigerate until ready to use for later or bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour, basting at intervals.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: In a small casserole dish, spray nonstick spray.
In a bowl, mix soup, milk and tuna.
Crush potato chips.
Layer chips and soup mix and chips and soup mix, finishing off with a layer of chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: crazy crust cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over margarine. Spoon fruit and juice (any kind) over mixture. Don't be stingy.

title: carciofi imbottiti(stuffed artichokes)
directions: Cut off tips of artichokes, about 1/2 to 3/4-inches.
Remove outer leaves.
Wash carefully.
Tap on table to spread leaves apart.
Shake out all water.

title: chicken and spinach enchiladas
directions: Combine
spinach,
soups
and
sour
cream in one bowl. Combine chicken,
onion
and
part	of cheese in another bowl. Soften tortillas
(12) in microwave for 1 minute.
Put chicken mixture in	tortillas and roll up.	Place in a baking dish and cover with	soup
mixture
and
remaining cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: cecil's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Boil together margarine, cocoa, oil and water.
Pour hot mixture over dry flour and sugar.
Add eggs; beat and then add buttermilk, soda and cinnamon.
Beat and pour into greased 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: juanita backus' harvard beets
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until thick; add butter and beets. Cook slow for about 10 minutes.

title: tomato pork chops
directions: Lightly spray an 8 x 8-inch oven casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
Add pork chops.
Place in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, turning once and allowing the meat to start cooking. Remove from oven.
Add rest of ingredients, starting with salt and pepper.
Also add onion and mushrooms.
Mix together the water and tomato soup; pour over pork chops.
Sprinkle with basil; cook for another 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Mix together except ginger ale.
This recipe freezes well. Delicious.

title: key lime cheesecake
directions: Mix and press into 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water and bring to a low boil.
Cut temperature to low and add soup and milk.
Stir constantly and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot alaska salmon melts
directions: Drain salmon; break into large chunks.
Add mayonnaise, parsley, onion, pimiento, lemon juice and pepper.
Toss gently to mix.
Fold in 1/2 cup cheese.
Spread about 1/4 cup mixture on each slice of bread.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over salmon mixture.
Broil about 6 inches from heat 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese melts and tops are golden.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese roll
directions: Grate cheddar cheese and mix with cream cheese and pecans. Shape into rolls. Roll in chili pepper until coated. Chill until form enough to slice. Serve on crackers of your choice.

title: easy chocolate cookies
directions: Stir it all together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yum!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oats, in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and mix in oats.
Pour into a cookie sheet.
Let cool, cut into squares and serve.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: In a skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, drained mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Unroll one package of crescent rolls and separate into triangles.
Place in a lightly greased pie plate, pressing edges together to form pie shell. Separate one of the eggs; set yolk aside.
Beat egg white with the remaining 2 eggs.
Pour 1/2 the beaten egg over pie shell.
Spoon meat mixture into shell.
Arrange the cheese slices atop; spread rest of beaten egg on cheese.
Mix reserved egg yolk with water; lightly brush some over edge of pastry.
Reserve rest.

title: celery root puree
directions: Place celery root and lemon juice in boiling salted water in a large saucepan. Cook, covered, over medium heat until tender, 15 to 40 minutes, depending on the size of the root. Drain. Mix butter and cream in a large mixer bowl. Add celery root. Beat until fluffy, about 10 minutes. Taste and adjust seasoning. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Makes 4 servings.

title: sliced squash casserole
directions: Pour melted butter into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add squash; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine egg, mayonnaise, onion and sugar; mix well and pour over squash.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: santa's snow delight
directions: Mix together in bowl the cream cheese, whipped topping and powdered sugar.
Spread this over wafer base.
Layer with strawberries, pineapple and whipped cream.
Top with pecans or walnuts.

title: banana muffins
directions: Beat with mixer.
Spray muffin pans with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cream chicken primavera
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine.
Add chicken; cook until no longer pink.
Add pasta, vegetables and water.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream; heat thoroughly.

title: tiny cheese biscuits
directions: Working with hands or electric mixer, blend cheese and butter into sifted dry ingredients until smooth.
Pat or roll on floured surface to about 1/3-inch thickness.
Cut with inside of doughnut or other small cutter.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all except 1/4 cup catsup. Shape into loaf in shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with the 1/4 cup catsup. Bake 25 minutes longer until done.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: jackie's scrumptiously delicious easy gourmet hot cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into a tart or pie pan. Sprinkle with bread crumbs (optional).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until bubbly.

title: 4 bean enchiladas
directions: Drain beans.
Combine beans and soup.
Heat tortillas in microwave (leave in bag).
Combine enchilada sauce and tomato sauce.
Pour enough sauce in 9 x 13-inch cake pan to cover bottom. Fill tortillas with bean mixture.
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Melt margarine. In small bowl, combine sugar and margarine.
Roll biscuits into 9-inch ropes and form circle.
Dip into margarine, then into the sugar/cinnamon mix.
Twist circle into figure 8.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch thick strips.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add beef strips.
Cook, stirring frequently, until brown.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Cover and simmer for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add green peppers for the last 5 minutes of simmering.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce: stir in beef mixture.
Cook until thickens. Boil about 1 minute.
Place tomatoes on top of mixture.
Water chestnuts may be added.
Cover and cook until heated.
Serve over rice.

title: stuffing
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute onion and celery until tender, about 15 minutes.
Add to bread with salt, pepper and sage.

title: crab gumbo
directions: In
heavy 8 quart pot make a caramel colored brown roux using 1/2 cup cooking oil and 1/2 cup flour.
Add to the roux, cooking until limp the onion, celery, bell pepper, garlic and parsley. Add
6 cups water, can of tomatoes, okra (optional), salt,
black pepper, crushed red pepper, bay leaves and thyme. Simmer for about
hour.
If it becomes too thick, add more water.
After 1 hour add 1 pound shrimp, crab meat and oysters (optional).
Simmer 30
minutes
longer.
Add
gumbo file (to taste).
Simmer 10 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: multi grain bread
directions: Note:
All rolled oats can be used.

title: fried pies
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients; add milk.
Roll out in small circles; fill with cooked fruit.
Fry at 380° in electric skillet or bake at 375°.

title: trout ala phred
directions: Catch a large trout at Lake Taupo, New Zealand.
Prepare as above and marinate in lemon juice, soy sauce, salt and pepper at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: chinese doodles
directions: Melt chips in top of double boiler.
Add chow mein noodles and peanuts. Drop from teaspoon on waxed paper. Let set.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and 3/4 cup sugar three times.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff. Add remaining sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Fold in thoroughly; add vanilla with addition of sugar.
Sift flour over top, a little at a time and fold in lightly with a down, up and over motion.
Pour in ungreased tube pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Invert pan to cool.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: *Or use 1 (16 ounce) jar spaghetti sauce and 1 1/4 cups water.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: In large glass bowl, crumble beef.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes on High, until beef is browned, stirring once; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss gently.
Cover and chill well prior to serving.

title: sugarless health cookies(diet cookies)
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Chop dates and nuts.
Put raisins in hot water to soften.
Mix and sift dry ingredients and add nuts and fruits to this mixture.
Beat egg until fluffy and add sweetener (dissolve in a little water first).
Add the creamed butter.
Then add flour mixture in thirds.
Stir just enough to combine the ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Each cookie has 51 calories.
Exchange 2 cookies for 1 fruit exchange and 1 fat exchange.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 18 cookies.

title: coconut pecan cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add egg.
Blend vanilla and coconut into mixture.
Refrigerate dough for 3 hours.
Shape into balls and roll in 1/2 cup coconut.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press pecan half into top of cookie.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Can be glazed with white Karo syrup while cookies are still hot. Yields 4 dozen.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Add all ingredients to a greased casserole dish.
Mix well with fork.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving so melted margarine will drain back in.

title: mint stay up all nights
directions: You may use 1 small package plain chocolate chips and mint extract if mint chocolate chips are unavailable.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place cut-up fryer in enough water to cover it all.
Add salt, pepper and onion.
Boil until tender, but not falling apart. Remove chicken from broth, but save broth.
Skim off excess fat.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken in tomato sauce with mini matzoh balls
directions: Prepare mini matzoh balls and set aside.
Slice an onion and place in bottom of pan in small amount of oil.
Remove skin from chicken and braise for several minutes on each side.
Drain off excess oil.
Add tomato sauce, enough to cover chicken (allow for extra sauce since matzoh balls will absorb a sufficient amount). Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook on low to medium heat for approximately 1 hour.
Add matzoh balls into sauce and cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight. Serve with ginger snap cookies.

title: easy pineapple pie
directions: Mix together and stir until thick.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: dressed up cabbage
directions: Add water according to amount of cabbage; put all in saucepan and steam for about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: working man's casserole
directions: Open sardines and chop them up.
Add chopped onion.
Stir well. Serve with saltine crackers and a cold drink.

title: dutch pea soup
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, and simmer at least an hour. If soup becomes too thick add a little water as needed.

title: pork loin roast
directions: Mix together; spread over roast.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in frypan. Stir in salt and pepper. Drain off excess grease. Place meat in long casserole dish and top with the mashed potatoes, then cheese. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake approximately 15 minutes at 400° until good and hot and cheese is melted.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour hard into meat.
Season and brown in fat.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: hidden valley ranch chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet or wok.
Add the chicken and the salad dressing.
Mix to coat chicken.
Add the vegetables and water.
Stir-fry about 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon crown cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour a tube pan. In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, margarine, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon half of batter in prepared pan.
Stir nuts, oats, brown sugar, cinnamon and applesauce into other half of batter. Spoon over batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: suckers
directions: Do not stir.
Boil until 310°.
Pour into another bowl and add food coloring and flavoring.
Stir well.
Butter molds; pour into molds and chill for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break bacon into small pieces.
Blend Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Toss with broccoli.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together.
Beat egg well.
Add milk.
Stir oil and lemon juice together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Add liquid ingredients. Microwave until thick, stirring every minute. Add enough ketchup to color. Serve over rice and chicken.

title: condiment for everything
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Mix sugar and cider and pour over other ingredients.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Mix dry ingredients together and add along with carrot, vanilla, coconut, pineapple and walnuts.
Mix carefully until blended.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased 9 inch square pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mrs. dwight copeland's stuffed dates
directions: Stuff each date with a pecan half. Make a dough using the margarine, cheese, paprika and flour.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Put a teaspoon of dough around each date, forming it into a football shape.
Place 3-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut candy(childrens recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls, then roll in finely chopped nuts.
This is a no cook delicious candy. Children love it.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato juice.
Put into a loaf. Pour tomato juice over top and cover tightly. Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fish fillets in shallow baking pan or dish.
Brush fish lightly with cooking oil.
Shake on Jane's Krazy Mixed-Up salt. Sprinkle with corn flakes.
With preheated oven at 500°, bake them from 14 to 18 minutes, depending on the thickness of fillets.

title: pat's fruit salad
directions: Cut up a variety of summer fruits.
Try to drain as much as possible.
To keep fresh looking, sprinkle on "So Fresh" citric acid.

title: peanut butter stacks(real good)
directions: Spread peanut butter between two crackers (like a sandwich). Melt Gurley almond bark.
Dip sandwich cracker into melted bark and cool on waxed paper.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Sift the flour with the cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Mix as butter cake. Form dough in rolls and wrap in waxed paper. Refrigerate, slice and bake as needed.

title: ernie's wimp wings
directions: Mix egg and milk together and coat chicken with mixture. Place flour in bag with 2 to 3 pieces of chicken at a time and place into hot oil and cook until brown.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and place cooked chicken into mixture and coat thoroughly.
Remove and eat.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Drain juice off sauerkraut.
Fry bacon until crispy.
Break or cut up.
Using bacon grease (do not toss away), add drained sauerkraut.
Brown.
Add water, sugar, onion and if you purchased sauerkraut without caraway, then add caraway seed.
Cover; simmer 50 to 60 minutes, until water disappears or take off cover at the end.
Sprinkle a little flour over to thicken.

title: beer doggies
directions: Mix the wieners, beer, catsup, brown sugar and onion in a saucepan; simmer for about an hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Mix well, scraping bowl often and mixing for 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pans.

title: tuna antipasto salad
directions: Drain all ingredients.
Saute peppers in small amount of oil. Drain.
Add all ingredients, except tuna.
Mix well.
Heat on medium for 10 minutes.
Add tuna and toss lightly.
Remove from heat.
Chill and serve on a platter.

title: garlic roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine all of the ingredients in a large bowl. Toss to coat well. Spread in jelly-roll pan.
Roast 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 285 calories.

title: baked corn dish
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.
When half through, stir, then finish baking.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook hamburger and cut-up onions in large skillet.
Cook potatoes and carrots together.
Blend or finely mince tomatoes. Combine all but mixed vegetables into skillet with hamburger. When ready to serve, stir in mixed vegetables.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and yolks of eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla, baking soda and sour cream.
Add flour.
Beat whites of eggs until stiff. Fold into flour mixture.
Pour half of batter in loaf pan. Sprinkle with half of the chopped walnuts mixed with sugar and cinnamon.
Top with remaining batter and sprinkle rest of walnut mixture on top of batter.
Heat oven to 350° and bake 1 hour.

title: chicken with vegetables, chinese style
directions: Toss the first 4 ingredients in oil and saute for 5 minutes. Push chicken to one side of the pan and add the celery, pepper and onion.
Stir and fry for 5 minutes and then add tomato, wine and soy sauce.
Heat to simmering.
Turn heat low, cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Then blend cornstarch and water and stir into chicken mixture.
Stir constantly until sauce bubbles.
Serve at once over crisp bean sprouts, rice or noodles.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix persimmon pulp, beaten eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together, pour liquid mixture into them.
Stir in melted butter.
Pour into shallow oiled pan to depth of about 2 inches.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
When cold, cut into squares and serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: cherry-ginger pandowdy
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease an 8-inch cake pan. Pour in pie filling and set aside.
In a medium size bowl, combine baking mix, sugar and ginger.
In a small bowl, combine margarine, milk and egg.
Blend well with fork.
Stir into baking mix mixture until smooth.
Spoon dough evenly over pie filling in cake pan. Bake about 40 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool for 20 minutes on wire rack.
Cut around edge of pan. Turn out on serving plate with cake on bottom.
Spread thickened juice around side of cake.
Press walnuts around side of cake.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: crock-pot beef stroganoff
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot and cook 6 hours on high, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender in small amount of water; drain. Combine carrots, onion and green pepper; set aside.
Combine soup, vinegar, salad oil, sugar and mustard.
Stir until well mixed. Pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly with a fork.
Refrigerate overnight.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger meat, onion soup, egg, bread crumbs and form into bite-sized meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 17 minutes.
Place on a cookie sheet for baking, they do not need to be turned.

title: prize meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well and press into ungreased baking dish or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: i can't believe it's a cookie cookie
directions: Stir peanut butter, sugar and eggs until well mixed.
Stir in vanilla.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet 2-inches apart; mash balls with a fork.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool completely before removing from pan.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar and beat well in mixer.
Add evaporated milk, bananas, pecans, vanilla and small amount of milk and mix well.
Pour in freezer, add enough milk to fill freezer within 2-inches from top.

title: maraschino party cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, juice and cherries and milk.
Mix well.
Add unbeaten egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes, scraping sides and bottom of bowl; fold in nuts.
Set oven at 350°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cool veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Unroll crescent dough; separate into 8 triangles.
On 13 inch round baking pan, arrange triangles in a circle with points in the center and wide ends toward the outside.
Using lightly floured roller, roll out dough to a 12-inch circle, pressing seams together to seal.
Bake 12 - 15 minutes or until light golden brown. Remove from oven. Cool completely.

title: monkey ball bread
directions: Cut rolls into fourths. Place in a plastic bag with granulated sugar and cinnamon. Shake to cover all balls of dough. Layer in greased Bundt pan. Melt margarine/butter in a small pan. Add brown sugar. Mix well and bring to a boil; boil 1 minute. Add nuts. Pour mixture over dough balls in pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes, then turn upside down on a plate. Eat, eat and eat!

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Let stand to cool. Refrigerate for several hours.
Roll out thin on a floured board, cut in desired squares and place on an ungreased cookie sheet to freeze.
Loosen with spatula and put in plastic bags to freeze. They can be used without freezing.
Cook in boiling chicken broth for 15 minutes or until tender.

title: pasta vert
directions: Peel and mash avocados with lemon juice in a large warm bowl. Add onion,	cheese, butter, cream and pasta.
Mix well. Serve immediately.

title: cheese and mushroom manicotti
directions: Combine all ingredients except manicotti and spaghetti sauce and set aside.
Mix the spaghetti sauce with 1 cup of water. Place half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stuff the manicotti shells with mixture and place in tomato sauce in pan.
Pour remaining sauce on top.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 375°.
Remove foil and sprinkle with grated cheese and place in oven until melted.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix with spoon until well blended.
Press in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: peach drink
directions: Mix the ingredients in a blender and serve.

title: mom messore spaghetti sauce(new york state fair winner)
directions: Fry garlic cloves in olive oil with diced onion.
In large kettle, combine with tomato paste, tomato sauce, whole tomatoes, water and all spices.
Simmer with meat balls.

title: perky pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Rinse with cold water.
Cook beans until crisp-tender.
Rinse with cold water.
Combine beans, tomatoes, meat, cheese, olives, cucumber and macaroni.
Whisk together oil, vinegar, mustard, parsley, sugar, cayenne pepper, paprika and garlic.
Pour over salad; toss and add basil to taste. Refrigerate at least 1 hour prior to serving.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt margarine, then add cocoa and milk.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Slice cake in 1-inch slices and line pan with angel food cake. Mix Dream Whip according to package instructions.
Add powdered sugar and softened cream cheese.
Spoon over cake.
Spoon strawberry freezer jam on top.
Refrigerate.

title: carrots
directions: Cook carrots in 1/2-inch boiling water for 8 minutes.
Drain water and pour carrots in casserole dish.
Melt oleo, add ginger and raisins.
Pour over carrots.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna in a shell
directions: Mix all but cantaloupe together.
Mound in cantaloupe halves.

title: hot three bean salad
directions: Microwave the bacon on High in a 2-quart casserole.
Remove bacon, leaving grease.
Mix dry ingredients and vinegar; microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Add beans and onion; microwave on High 6 minutes, covered.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add bacon.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Layer fruits in a large bowl in order given.
Spoon orange juice concentrate on top.
Cover and chill 6 to 8 hours.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: 14 day slaw
directions: Sliver the cabbage fine and slice the onion fine.
Slice bell pepper and grate carrot finely.
Sprinkle sugar over this.
Bring to a boil oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt to taste.
Pour this over your cabbage and let set for 14 days in refrigerator.

title: meat loaf
directions: Fold all ingredients together; sprinkle crumbs over loaf. Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes, then decrease oven temperature to 250°.
Bake for about an hour or until done.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Let cool.
Add egg and mix together.
Add yeast dissolved in warm water.
Add flour.
Let rise 1 hour and then work down.
Roll out dough and spread with butter. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and slice.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
The quantity of butter, sugar and cinnamon is measured by your own judgment.

title: good hot dish
directions: Cook macaroni dinner.
Brown hamburger.
Cook vegetables and add butter.
Mix macaroni dinner with hamburger and soups together. Top with vegetables.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Brown ground meat and onion.
Layer corn bread mixture, ground meat mixture and grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana bran bread
directions: Blend together shortening, honey, bran, eggs, and banana. mixing really well. Sift together and add flour, baking soda and salt. Pour into a greased 8 1\2 x 4 1\2 x 2 1\2 pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until done. Cool on wire rack. Make 1 loaf.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light; add eggs.
Beat well. Stir flour and baking powder and add to cream mixture alternately with milk.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook 1 hour at 350° in a large iron skillet.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix fruit with sugar and chill overnight.
Drain off juice. Add whipped cream, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix and let set a few hours in the refrigerator before serving.

title: salmon teriyaki
directions: * Good also with tuna or Mahi-Mahi (Dolphin steaks).

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake as directed, except use, crushed pineapple and juice in place of the water.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed.

title: chocolate chip toffee grahams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break graham crackers into squares. Arrange graham cracker squares in a single layer in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly-roll pan.
Set aside.
Combine butter and sugar in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until butter melts.
Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in cinnamon and pecans.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt semi sweet chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in microwave on medium for 6 or 7 minutes, stirring every minute so it will not burn. Stir in peanuts. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Cool.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cream well.
Beat in egg until fluffy; add vanilla.
Stir together remaining dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Roll out dough on lightly floured board and cut.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned.

title: pechay (bok choy) with ground beef
directions: Saute garlic and onions until golden brown.
Add ground beef. Season it and let it simmer until almost dry, then add the hard part of peachy or bok choy first.
Pour 5 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Add the beef broth when it starts to boil and after 2 minutes, drop the rest of the pechay or bok choy leaves.
Cook for 2 minutes more and it will be ready to serve after seasoning it according to your taste.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix jello, pineapple with syrup and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish; chill at least 3 hours.

title: casserole carrots
directions: Pare carrots; slice diagonally, then place in casserole. Sprinkle top with sugar and salt.
Add water; dot with butter. Cover; bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until carrots are tender.

title: chris' salsa
directions: Mix together.
Chop in a blender or use a salsa maker.
Keep refrigerated.

title: citrus eye-opener
directions: In a gallon container, combine the orange juice concentrate, lemonade concentrate and 1 cup water.
Cover the container; chill in the refrigerator until serving time.
Just before serving, slowly add carbonated water; stir gently to mix.
Serve over ice. Hook orange wedges on side of glasses or float in punch.
Makes about 8 (10-ounce) servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well with mixer.
Add 1 egg at a time, continuing to beat.
Add extract and then flour and mix.
Remove from mixer and fold in 7-Up.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Use as a dip for raw vegetables.
Makes 1 quart.

title: blue cheese spread
directions: Using an electric mixer, blend the Blue cheese.
Add cream cheese and raw onion (finely chopped).
Add the dried parsley and mix until smooth.

title: calypso bars
directions: Melt chocolate in hot water over low heat.
Add sugar (white) and stir until dissolved.
Add dates; cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup butter.
Blend in vanilla; cool.

title: djupa droppar(fritters)
directions: Combine sugar and milk, then add eggs and butter.
Sift dry ingredients and add, using just enough flour to make a fairly stiff batter, but not too stiff!
Drop by teaspoonfuls into 375° fat and fry like doughnuts.
When cool, shake in a sack with powdered sugar.
Powder again before serving.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Eat with vegetables or chips.

title: country pie
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, onion, bell pepper, seasoning and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Press into a 9 or 10-inch pie pan forming a shell.
Mix rice, cheese and remaining tomato sauce.
Pour into meat shell.
Sprinkle top with a little additional cheese after it has baked a while.
Bake at 350° for a total of 35 to 40 minutes until meat is done.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix puddings and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Butter bottom of pan. Put a layer of crackers.
Pour half of pudding mixture over graham crackers.
Add another layer of crackers; pour remaining pudding over this.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.
Spread chocolate icing over crackers.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: sour cream and cinnamon fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh fruit. Makes 1 cup.

title: frozen citrus pie
directions: Beat concentrate in large bowl approximately 30 seconds. Blend in ice cream.
Fold in whipped topping until smooth.
Freeze if necessary until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm 4 hours or overnight. Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.

title: no bake breakfast cookies
directions: Stir honey and peanut butter together in medium pan over low heat.
Remove pan from heat and stir in dry milk.
Fold in cereal flakes and raisins.
Roll into small balls and place on waxed paper.
Cool to room temperature.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 10 to 12 cookies.

title: polpettoni saporiti
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix first five ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce.
On waxed paper, press mixture into 12 x 7-inch rectangle.
Cut crosswise into 6 strips.
Mix rice, green peppers and 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce.
Divide rice mixture into 6 parts.
Put into center of strips.
Fold meat over rice, shaping each into a loaf.
Put on baking sheet.
Spoon 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce over loaves.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: summer salad boil
directions: Drain all canned vegetables, then mix with fresh vegetables. Pour cooled marinade over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: salsa
directions: For chunky style, finely chop onion, garlic, cilantro and peppers.
You may want to remove the seeds from peppers before chopping them, because the more seeds, the hotter the sauce.
Mix together and add the tomatoes, lime juice, salt and pepper.
Mix well until the tomatoes are partially liquefied but lumpy.
For smoother salsa, put all in a blender till smooth.
Keep in refrigerator for 2-3 hours before serving.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter, then roll in mixture of crushed Ritz crackers and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: flat dumplings
directions: Sift flour into mixing bowl. Hollow out center; work shortening into flour in hollow. Mix together beaten egg, salt and milk and pour into hollow. Work in flour from edges until stiff dough is formed. Roll out on floured board until very thin. Cut into 1-inch strips and stretch while pulling off pieces about 1 1/2 or 2-inches long and drop into boiling broth. Keep boiling until tender.

title: heaven on earth
directions: Bake brownie mix as directed.
Cool and crumble into pieces. Mix mousse as directed on package.
Freeze candy bars and break into pieces.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in a heavy pan.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
When mixture reaches boiling stage, stir in peanuts.
Cook on medium-low heat.
Stir frequently.
Cook until mixture reaches the hard crackling stage, 280° to 300°.
Add oleo and stir mixture.

title: quick quiche
directions: Mix
broccoli,
onion, peppers and cheese.
Sprinkle on bottom of
deep
dish
pie
pan
or quiche dish that has been buttered. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds by hand mixer or in blender.
Pour on top of other ingredients in
pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Let set 5 minutes, then
serve.
Slice like
pie.
Garnish
with
pepper
rings, onions or small tomatoes.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar;
add
eggs, beating after each addition.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to creamed ingredients alternately with
milk.
Add
potatoes, vanilla and nuts. Mix well and bake in
greased
and
floured
cake pans at 350° until done. Good with Buttermilk Icing or Cream Cheese Icing.

title: whole wheat banana nut bread
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; stir well and set aside. Combine butter and sugar; cream mixture until light and fluffy. Add egg and mix well. Combine bananas and buttermilk; add to creamed mixture. Alternate with dry ingredients. Mix in chopped pecans. Stir until combined. Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until bread tests done. Cool 10 minutes in pan; remove to wire rack and cool completely. Wonderful to freeze and pull out anytime.

title: tiny taco meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into meat balls.
Put foil on a baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, bring to a boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until dissolved and add vanilla and oatmeal.
Spoon out with teaspoon and place on waxed paper.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: hummingbird feed
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil until sugar melts.
Let cool and put in feeders.

title: quick christmas relish
directions: Put all vegetables through grinder.
Combine in pot; heat to boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cut carrots and celery into 3-inch long matchstick strips. Slice onion thin.
Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Cut mushrooms into quarters.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine water and 2 tablespoons picante in shallow dish. Place tortillas in mixture and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cook ground beef with onion until brown.
Drain.
Stir in salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder, garlic powder, olives and remaining picante. Simmer 5 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan; add flour until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream and stir until well blended.
Place 1/2 of tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 sour cream mixture over tortillas, then 1/2 meat mixture and then 1/2 cheese.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Twist off stems of large mushrooms.
Set aside the caps. Mince stems, 1/2 pound mushrooms and green onions.
Heat them with butter on medium-high heat until all water is boiled away.
Add cream cheese, dill and Parmesan and blend mixture well.
Place large mushroom caps on cookie sheet and stuff with mixture.
Broil until browned and bubbly.

title: jello red cherry salad
directions: Heat cherries, sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Pour over jello and stir until dissolved.
Allow to cool and add cola, pineapple and nuts.
Let it set some, then stir and put in mold.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme thoroughly.
Serve with strawberries, pear slices or other fruit.
Makes 16 servings.

title: spicy spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat in big pot until dark brown, letting it stick a little.
While browning, add chopped onion and finely chopped garlic to brown also.
Cover meat with red pepper while browning (more or less to suit your taste).
Add tomato sauce and reduce heat.
Stir occasionally while covered sauce simmers. Simmer 40 to 45 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed.
Shred Velveeta cheese and sprinkle atop noodles and sauce.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, vegetable shortening, milk, margarine, eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer at medium speed for 20 minutes, scraping down sides occasionally.
Pour into pan.

title: lemon-apricot cake
directions: Mix. Bake in prepared tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, water and oil.
Next, combine salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, flour and baking soda.
Add this mixture to pumpkin.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour mixture into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Coat bottom of large pan with olive oil.
Add chopped garlic and cook until soft.
Add tomato paste with 1/2 can of water and simmer for a few minutes.
Add spices and then add tomato sauce and simmer for several hours.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine; cook covered in 250° oven for 5 hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Saute onions and peppers in 2 tablespoons butter until tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat; gradually stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in corn and egg.
Pour into an ungreased 1-quart casserole dish.
Stir cracker crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted butter together; sprinkle over corn.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy mints
directions: Combine butter and water.
Place over low heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat; add salt and extract.
Gradually add sugar, blending until desired consistency is reached.
If colored candies are desired, divide candy in parts and tint various shades, by dropping food coloring.
Knead until smooth.
Mold into individual candies or form small rolls to sliced.
If rolls are refrigerated, allow to return to room temperature before slicing.

title: eggless, milkless chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, cocoa and soda into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix in order and pour into ungreased pan. Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Mash with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In large bowl, mix soup, milk, mustard and pepper.
Stir in macaroni and 3 cups cheese.
Spoon into 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbling; stir.

title: quail a la moore
directions: Bring rice to boil in two cups of water and bouillon cubes, stir.
Boil until rice begins to flake (25 minutes).

title: strawberry chantilly
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin and water in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil and is clear.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Thoroughly blend in Cool Whip.
Chill until firm (about 3 hours).
Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Top with strawberries.
Makes 4 cups or 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry topped lemon cheese cake
directions: With a mixer, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk, lemon juice, and vanilla extract.
Pour into crust and chill at least
three hours before topping with pie filling.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on cookie sheet about 1/2-inch thick.
Put in freezer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from freezer and cut into squares.
Flour and brown both sides.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with 1 can undiluted mushroom soup.
Tomato soup or chicken soup is good also.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
If more mixture than needed, freeze for another meal.

title: guacamole salad
directions: In medium-size bowl, combine avocados, tomato, cucumber, scallion, lime juice, garlic, cilantro, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Toss gently but thoroughly to mix.

title: portabella mushrooms
directions: Mix corn starch into cold beef broth.
Heat in large skillet. Stir frequently.
As broth thickens add garlic powder, soy sauce and red wine.
Heat until mixture is thick and dark brown.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and simmer until mushrooms are cooked.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add salt, pineapple, grated cheese and onion.
Mix together with mixer.
Add 1/2 cup of pecans, finely chopped.
Shape mixture into a ball.
Cover with remaining whole pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: kotlet
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Take a little portion, roll into a ball and then flatten.
(It should be the size of a hamburger.)
Put some bread crumbs on both sides of the patty.
Fry in an oiled frying pan on both sides.

title: oriental salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the lettuce, water chestnuts, bean sprouts, fresh spinach, bacon and boiled eggs.
In
a separate bowl,
prepare the dressing by whisking together the oil, sugar, vinegar, onion, worcestershire and salt.
Toss the dressing with the salad and serve.

title: slush
directions: Take 7 cups water with 2 cups sugar and bring to a boil. Cool.
Put tea bags with 2 cups boiling water.
Mix tea water with sugar water.
Add frozen orange juice and lemonade.
Add liquor. Mix.
Freeze.

title: fried apple pies (turnovers)(very old recipe)
directions: Prepare apples and set aside to cool.
You may use canned apples or apple butter.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Stir together eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Add dry ingredients. Stir just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400°
for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: preserved vegetable marrow(popular in britain)
directions: Peel marrow and cut into small pieces.
Put in cold water with a little salt and let it remain 12 hours.
Take it out on a large meat dish, have an equal quantity of loaf sugar.

Sprinkle 1 pound over the marrow to remain all night, then add the remainder of the sugar, juice and peel of 2 lemons, 2 ounces whole ginger, bruised, and 1 dozen cayenne pods, tied up in a piece of muslin.
Boil gently until marrow becomes quite clear and the juice rather thick. Should there be any seeds, take them out, also the ginger, peel and pods when you put into jars.
Preserve only the firm ones.
The spices and lemons are sufficient for 4 pounds marrow.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt
marshmallows.
Add
small can cream and mix well. Add rest
of ingredients.
Put in a pan or glass dish and pat with hands
until pressed in dish good.
Put in icebox until firm and ready for slicing.	Keep in icebox.

title: candy coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar on medium heat until mixed.
Add peanuts, stirring until liquid covers peanuts.
Pour on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Combine
marinade
ingredients.
Put chicken in shallow baking dish
and	pour
marinade over.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Turn chicken pieces occasionally.	Preheat oven to 375°.
Line broiler pan with foil and arrange chicken on rack (slotted top
of broiler pan) or can use foil lined baking pan and rack.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.	Baste occasionally with leftover marinade while it's baking.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Cook in microwave on High, covered, 14 to 18 minutes, stirring twice.

title: blueberry pinwheel cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Stir well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Stir in vanilla and lemon juice.
Set aside.

title: taco casserole(microwave)
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Add cheese, soup and sauce, mixing well.
Place corn chips in glass baking dish.
Pour hamburger mixture over chips.
Microwave on High until cheese is melted.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in double boiler until hot.
Don't boil. After all is hot, pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans if desired.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
This will set up as it cools.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; stir in sugar, syrup and margarine.
Stir in pecans and add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lime squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar. Press in ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan, building up 1/2-inch edges.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Add flour and buttermilk. Melt chocolate and add 1/2 cup hot water.
Add to batter.
Bring to boil the other 1/2 cup of hot water.
Add soda and immediately add to batter.
Add vanilla last.
Bake in a greased loaf pan filled 3/4 full.
(There will be extra batter for cupcakes.)
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mush(melkegrot)
directions: Set table before starting.
Scald milk and salt on medium-high setting until slightly steaming and skin on top.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: If using canned peaches, drain well and reduce sugar to 3/4 cup.

title: corn fritters
directions: Heat 2 to 3 inches of Crisco in deep fryer or deep saucepan. Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt in large bowl. Combine eggs, milk and 2 teaspoons melted shortening in medium bowl.
Stir in corn.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened. Drop by tablespoon, a few at a time, in hot shortening heated to 365°.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn as needed. Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm with syrup.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Fry bacon crisp; drain on paper towel.
Saute onions in bacon fat until golden brown.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Pour over sliced potatoes.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: oatmeal (mock pecan pie)
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Put in pie crust and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not double this batch.

title: nacho sauce
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese in a crock-pot.
Add beef, salsa and beans in cheese.
After cheese is smooth, turn crock-pot down on low.
Stir occasionally to prevent burning.
Serve with nacho chips or bread sticks.

title: famous v.f.w. kruschicki(post 7251)
directions: Mix all together; roll out and cut in 2 1/2 inch squares.
Put a slit in center and pull one end through slit.
Fry in deep oil. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: coconut balls
directions: Thoroughly mix coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Divide mixture into 2 small mixing bowls.
Add 1/2 package lime Jell-O to one bowl and 1/2 package strawberry Jell-O to the other bowl.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate overnight.
Form small balls from cold mixture and roll in corresponding remaining Jell-O.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flavoring, then eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Alternate flour and whipping cream, using small amounts at a time.
Mix well.
Turn batter into tube pan.
Do not grease pan.
Start baking in cold oven set at 350°.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Delicious!

title: skillet chicken spaghetti
directions: In skillet, cook sausage 3 minutes; add chicken.
Sprinkle with oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
When chicken is browned, drain. Add noodles and 1 cup water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 17 minutes over medium heat or until chicken and spaghetti are cooked.

title: diet apple pie
directions: Place undrained apples in dish. Slice up most of the butter and place it in dish with apples. Microwave on high for 2 minutes. Stir in cornstarch and cinnamon. Mix well and microwave for 2 more minutes. Add Equal and mix thoroughly. Place mixture in one pie shell. Use other shell to form a top crust. Pick top with fork and place pats of butter on top of pie. Bake in 400° oven for 20 min.

title: mary ola's pie
directions: Note:
Must spread with Cool Whip before trying to cut.

title: hoppin' john(a traditional new years special)
directions: Rinse beans.
Cover with water and let soak overnight or for quick cook, bring beans and water to a boil; boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Chop lettuce, tomatoes and onion; place in a large bowl. Brown beef and add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in beans and warm through.
At the last minute, toss all ingredients together and mix thoroughly.
Serves 4 to 6 generously.

title: inspiration salad
directions: Place macaroni, ham and vegetables in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over salad ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute together sausage, onions and peppers until sausage is done.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Pour in sausage mixture.
Cover with beaten eggs.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until center is done.
Sprinkle grated cheeses over top.
Return to oven until melted.
(Good for breakfast.)

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and butter to boil and boil 1 minute. Add peanut butter, oats, vanilla and coconut and mix well. Drop on waxed paper.
Coconut may be omitted if you like.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream sugar, shortening and vanilla; add eggs, one at a time.
Add water alternately with dry ingredients to egg and sugar mixture.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In large baking dish, put chicken soup, mushroom soup, rice and water.
Add chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: never fail icing
directions: Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Flavor with vanilla and butter to taste.
Cool and beat until right consistency.
If it gets too thick or hard, add a little milk and stir.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into 2 balls.
Refrigerate.
Can roll one ball in parsley flakes.

title: lemon thyme sauce
directions: In a blender, whip the cottage cheese.
Combine all of the ingredients in a small bowl.
Serve over fish or vegetables, such as baked potatoes or you can add 2 tablespoons more milk and serve as a salad dressing.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Prepare a single crust pie shell and cook until golden brown. Cook the first three ingredients in a double boiler until very thick and remove from heat.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and butter, mix well.
Cook one batch of pie filling and pour it into the cooked pie shell, cook a second batch and pour over the first batch.
Top with meringue.
Place under a broiler until meringue is golden. Chill before serving.

title: louisiana chess pie
directions: Beat sugar and oleo together until well creamed. Add eggs, one at a time; mix well after each (do not use electric mixer). Add other ingredients and mix well, but do not overmix. Place in 3 uncooked shells and bake at 375° for about 35 minutes until medium brown.

title: sugar-free fudge cake
directions: Use electric mixer lowest speed to combine first 3 dry ingredients thoroughly.
Put remaining liquid ingredients into blender, high just to blend well and pour into dry ingredients, beating high speed until smooth (3 minutes).
Spread batter evenly in greased, floured 9-inch Pyrex square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick into center comes out clean.
Sprinkle top of warm cake with hammered bits of a 2 1/2 ounce sugar-free Estee brand chocolate bar.
Cool in dish on rack before cutting to serve nine nicely.
(Freeze to thaw and serve in 6 months.)

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Mix cucumbers, salt and onion together.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Drain well.
Make syrup of vinegar and sugar.
Add the syrup to the cucumber mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: "you're a smart cookie" cookie
directions: Beat margarine and sugars.
Beat in egg, milk, vanilla, flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in oats and M&M's (save some to sprinkle on top).
Grease 2 pizza pans which are lined with aluminum foil.
Place half dough on each greased pizza pan and spread to 1-inch edge of pan.
Sprinkle remainder of M&M's over top of each large cookie.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake until golden brown, 15 to 17 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into wedges as desired.
Cookie sheets can be used instead of pizza pans.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Combine last 4 ingredients. Combine in order given including bananas.
Bake in an oiled and floured loaf pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Allow to stand until following day before cutting.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Saute sausage until browned.
Drain off fat and set meat aside.
Slice eggs and arrange half in 2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine in saucepan and blend in flour and seasoning.
Add milk and cook, stirring until thickened.
Add sausage and corn.
Mix well and pour over eggs in casserole.
Top with remaining eggs and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake in preheated 375° for 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: grandma carbonara's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown lamb shanks.
When almost cooked, add onions and garlic. Cook a minute, then add tomato sauce and paste.
Simmer until all is tender. Add the oregano, basil and parsley.
Let simmer 2 to 3 hours, adding water if needed.
About 1/2 hour prior to serving, place meatballs and sausage in sauce which has already been 3/4 cooked.

title: red green pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Place in colander to drain.
Make syrup of salt, vinegar, mustard seed and sugar; boil 30 minutes. Add onions and peppers and simmer for 30 minutes or until tender. Ladle into hot pint jars, filling within 1/2 inch of top.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream
together
the powdered sugar and margarine.
Add egg, salt and vanilla. Mix well until light and fluffy. Spread this on the two crusts. Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first four (4) ingredients together; set aside.
Put oleo in 2-quart casserole and place in 350° oven until melted.
Remove dish and mix together all ingredients and dump into 2-quart oleoed baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Generously butter a cookie sheet. In a large saucepan over high heat, cook sugar, water and corn syrup until mixture reaches 280 degrees on a candy thermometer. Slowly add nuts and stir until temperature reaches 300 degrees. Turn off heat. Carefully stir in butter and vanilla until blended. Add baking soda, and stir vigorously but cautiously. Pour mixture onto prepared cookie sheet and spread as thinly as possible with a wooden spoon. Cool completely, about 15 minutes, Break cooled candy into pieces or chop to make toppings for ice cream. Store in an an airtight container. Makes about 2 pounds.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oats, together.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats and mix well.
Stir and let stand for 2 minutes.
Drop onto wax paper with a teaspoon.

title: baked chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
In a large skillet, cook chicken in 2 tablespoons oleo about 5 minutes on each side, or until tender (can use more oleo).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange broccoli and chicken in a shallow 2 1/2 or 3-quart baking dish.
In a medium bowl, stir soup, mayonnaise, milk, mustard and pepper until blended.
Stir in cheese.
Spoon over chicken and broccoli.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
In a small bowl, mix bread crumbs, melted oleo and paprika.
Uncover chicken; sprinkle with crumbs mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: vegetable cheese bake
directions: Place cooked and drained broccoli pieces in shallow baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Blend soup, milk and cheese; pour over vegetable.
Top with crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until bubbling.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring last 4 ingredients to a boil and pour over remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Marinate overnight.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, and oil.
In separate bowl, drain and mix vegetables.
Add almond slivers.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: In medium bowl blend cream cheese, salad dressing and sugar. Fold in whipped topping; set aside.
In large mixing bowl combine pineapple, nuts, coconut and cranberry sauce.
Add cranberries if desired.
Gently combine with cream cheese mixture.
Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or three foil-lined 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares or slices and serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 24 servings.

title: no-fail pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup with mixer.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake until set, 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Enjoy!

title: tony's lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef, sausage, onion, salt, pepper and oregano on low heat. Turn over ingredients often.
Drain off grease.
While browning the meat, boil water for the lasagna noodles.
Put in 2 or 3 at a time.
Let boil 10 to 12 minutes. Drain, then do 3 more.
Grease loaf pan.
Put a tiny bit of sauce in pan. Lay 3 noodles down, then half the meat, oregano, garlic powder a little Ragu sauce (about 1/3) and a layer of Mozzarella or Provolone cheese. Repeat.
After placing the last 3 noodles, top with the rest of the sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Measure juice drained from pineapple.
Add water to make 1 pint.
Heat liquid to boiling; dissolve gelatin in liquid.
Add all other ingredients; stir well.
Put in mold or pan; chill in refrigerator.
Stir mixture several times.

title: quickie boston cream pie
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions.
Cool cake completely.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to package directions, using only 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Chill until set.
Cut cake into two thin layers.
Spread pudding onto one layer and top with second layer.
In a small bowl combine remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour glaze onto top of cake, allowing some to drizzle down the sides.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: hot pepper mustard
directions: Grind peppers in food blender; combine.
Cook until tender. Stir in last 5 ingredients.
Cook until thick.

title: skillet sausage peppers
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add peppers, onion and garlic; saute 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove.
Add sausage to skillet; saute 10 minutes or until browned.
Return peppers, garlic and onion to skillet.
Add tomatoes and oregano; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cook 12 to 14 minutes. Toss with egg noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mints
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Knead the powdered sugar and cream cheese together to make a stiff dough.
Divide mint mixture into as many bowls as you want different colors and flavors of mints.
Add only a few drops of coloring and flavoring at a time.
Roll mint mixture into balls the size of small marbles.
As each mint is made, dip it and the mold into granulated sugar. Press mixture into mold firmly.
Roll edges back from mold and tap mold upside down until mint drops out.
As the mints are made, place them face up on waxed paper to dry.
When all have dried for at least an hour or overnight, arrange in layers between waxed paper in airtight containers.
May be frozen.
Yields 250 leaves or 180 roses.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter a large casserole or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer potato, cabbage, onion and celery.
(Optional:
add a few chopped carrots.)
Top with ground beef.
Mix chicken soup, sour cream and milk and pour over casserole.
Bale uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: paradise pudding
directions: Combine rice, pineapple and marshmallows. Stir in cream. Chill before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 4 minutes and drain.
Add other ingredients. Melt 1 stick oleo.
Add crushed crackers and cover broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: terry's taco salad(serves 16 people)
directions: Assemble first 7 ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Brown hamburger.
Add drained kidney beans.
Put lid on frypan and turn heat to low until ready to serve.
When ready to serve, put meat/bean mixture into greens and toss lightly with salad dressing.

title: bake ahead sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Heat again before meal until cheese is bubbly. Sprinkle top with onion flakes, parsley flakes and paprika. Serves 4.

title: baking chocolate brownies
directions: Bake in a long cake pan at 350° for exactly 25 minutes.
Frost in pan with chocolate frosting (use the recipe on Hershey's baking chocolate package for Quick Chocolate Frosting).

title: grapefruit, avocado and red onion salad
directions: Peel grapefruit, being sure to remove all the white, then separate by removing the membranes from between the sections. Peel and slice avocado.
Mix with mayonnaise and garnish with red onion slices.

title: cole slaw
directions: Toss in large bowl.

title: tuna-cashew casserole
directions: Save 3/4 cup of noodles.
Mix rest of ingredients. Put in buttered dish.
Sprinkle the 3/4 cup of noodles over the top. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.
Can double for larger servings or company.

title: mom's oatmeal cookieshouston, texas
directions: Pre-heat oven to 400°.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oatmeal, raisins, walnuts, oil, eggs and milk.
Grease a baking sheet and spoon 1/2 tsp. of dough for each cookie onto the cookie sheet about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, until very lightly browned.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 1 deep dish pie or 2 small pies.

title: chocolate filbert clusters
directions: Spread filberts in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° until toasted, 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Rub off as much of the skins as possible with your hands.
Break chocolate into squares.
Place in top of double boiler over simmering (not boiling) water.
Stirring occasionally, heat chocolate until melted.
Remove from heat.
