Mix in instant coffee and oil until smooth and glossy.
Stir in nuts to coat well.
Drop filbert clusters by heaping teaspoonfuls onto buttered waxed paper on baking sheet.
Let stand at cool room temperature until set, then store airtight in a covered container in a cool place.
Yields 2 dozen confections.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients.
Spread mayonnaise on top in thin layer.
Top with grated cheese and crumbled bacon.

title: chili - quick
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef or turkey meat until crumbly; drain fat.
Add Lawry's chili mix, 1/2 cup water, 1 large can of chili and large can of kidney beans.
Add can of crushed tomatoes and chili powder.
This works well in a crock-pot on low for about 4 to 6 hours.
Add more chili powder to your taste.

title: beenie-weenies
directions: Saute onion and hot dogs in butter (not margarine) until brown.
Add beans and barbecue sauce to taste.
Lightly butter bread and sprinkle with garlic.
Spoon bean mixture on bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until hot.
Our kids favorite!!!

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices. Season with salt and pepper. Dredge slices in corn meal or flour to coat both sides. Heat grease in heavy skillet. Add tomatoes; fry slowly until browned, turning once.

title: aunt bonnie's chicken casserole
directions: In a large pan, on stove, melt margarine and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in the milk gradually and the broth.
Heat to almost boiling and simmer until thickened.
Add the rest of the ingredients to blend and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (in 13 x 9-inch plus a 10 x 8-inch size baking dishes or pans).
Be careful when blending margarine, flour and milk so it doesn't get lumpy.
Chop pimento, mushrooms and green pepper finely together before adding.

title: grandma mock's southern biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda into bowl.
Cut in shortening thoroughly (until mixture looks like meal).
Stir in almost all the milk.
If dough is not pliable, add just enough milk to make it a soft, puffy, easy to roll dough.
Knead on lightly floured board 20 to 25 times.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except spinach. Wash spinach well and drain. Break spinach into pieces. When ready to serve, put spinach on individual salad plates and spoon dressing on each salad.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: You will need an oblong glass baking dish.

title: banana breakfast bars
directions: Stir all together; pour into oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Freezes very well.

title: johnny m casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until done; drain.
Add tomato and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Drain noodles.
Layer hamburger mixture and noodles until casserole is full.
Cover with slices of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and cook until peanuts begin to pop.
Remove from stove and put the baking soda in while stirring.
Pour into greased bowl.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Mix real good.
Pour into crust.
If you like, sprinkle a little cinnamon over top of pie. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes longer or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: charlie's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in cornbread baking pan at 350° until done.

title: rice krispies treat
directions: Melt sugar and Karo together on medium
heat until dissolved. Remove from heat and add peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Pour into cake pan and press until packed lightly.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: kathy's pecan rolls
directions: Melt honey with butter.
Combine brown sugar with cinnamon. Dip rolls in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place rolls in bottom of greased cake pan, then pour honey and butter sauce over the rolls. Sprinkle the nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spanish cream
directions: Combine milk and gelatin and scald in double boiler.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks to which the sugar has been added. Cook until it coats the spoon, about 8 to 10 minutes; but be sure not to overcook.
Add 2 egg whites, beaten stiff and almond extract.
Chill before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix well whipped topping, sour cream and sugar.
Wash, clean and slice 2 pints of fresh strawberries.
Stack cake using lots of filling and 1/3 of the berries for each layer.
Cover sides of cake with remaining topping mix.
Refrigerate.

title: fried stuffing
directions: Cut up bread, celery and onion.
Saute onion and celery until tender.
Use
about
tablespoons margarine.
Mix with bread cubes, adding
chicken
bouillon.
If
not moist enough, add water.
Add beaten	egg,
salt, pepper and garlic.	Melt 4 tablespoons margarine in
frying pan.
Add stuffing mix.
Toss and allow to brown, adding margarine as needed.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Boil butter, cocoa and water.
Add sour milk, soda, vanilla and eggs to dry mixture.
Add butter, cocoa and water. Mix well and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grustili(italian cookies)
directions: Mix in order given to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth. Let rest 15 minutes.
Roll out in thin sheets (I use my noodle machine).
Cut into strips and fry in deep fat, turning when light tan.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Bring to boil 1 cup of sugar, 1/2 cup of oil, 1/2 cup of vinegar and 1 tablespoon of water.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cool, pour over vegetable mixture and refrigerate overnight.
It's ready to serve.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in lard. Beat water, vinegar and egg together.
Mix the lard mixture into flour.
Divide dough in half. Roll out each half and cut into 6 squares.
Peel and core 12 tart apples.
Place 1 apple on each square of crust.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and a dash of cinnamon.
Wrap crust around apple. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry and spinach salad
directions: To Make Dressing:
Combine olive oil, orange juice, vinegar, honey, poppy seed and mustard in a small bowl; stir well.

title: petite cranberry muffins
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar, egg and cottage cheese. Fold in cranberries and raisins by hand.
Mix in flour and remaining ingredients.
Stir together well, then fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake until puffed and lightly browned.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 24 petite little muffins.

title: room 189's pie crust
directions: Butter
sides
of
heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves
and mixture boils.
Cook without stirring to soft
ball stage
Immediately pour onto platter.
Do not
scrape pan.
Cool until candy feels only slightly warm to the
touch, about
minutes;
do not move.
Using a wooden spoon,
scrape candy from edge of platter toward center, then work until creamy and stiff.
Knead until smooth and free from lumps.
Wrap.
Place in
a
covered container to ripen for 24 hours.
Warm
ripened mixture in bowl over hot water and work to
a
smooth cream for about 2 minutes, adding a few drops of water if needed.
Work in almond paste until smooth.
Place in bowl.
Cover
with dampened cloth and let ripen several hours. Divide in parts;
tint
to desired
color with red, yellow or green food
coloring and shape into fruits as described below. Dry fruits overnight
on
their sides on wax paper.
Next day, add blushes of sugar.

title: chicken ala king
directions: In oil, saute green peppers and mushrooms.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Slowly add broth and milk.
Cook until smooth.
Add cream, pimiento, cooked chicken and seasoning.
Heat through.
Beat egg yolk.
Add a little hot sauce and add to remaining ingredients.

title: pizza dough
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 1/4 cups flour, yeast and salt.
Add warm water and oil.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds, then on high speed for 3 minutes.
Using a spoon, stir in as much of remaining flour as you can.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead in enough flour to make moderately stiff dough.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Yields 6 servings.

title: carole's easy lasagne(microwave)
directions: Set microwave power select at High.
Crumble ground beef into large glass bowl.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes or until beef is browned; stir once.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Meanwhile, combine Ricotta cheese, egg and pepper.
Spoon 1/2 cup of sauce in oblong baking dish.
Alternately layer uncooked noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella cheese and sauce, forming 2 layers.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Moisten with a little olive oil. Remove stems and fill.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, pepper and salt.
Pour and spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put 2 cans of green beans over your hamburger layer, then top with Tater Tots.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Pour evenly over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: possum dip
directions: In a large, deep skillet, brown the possum (or ground beef) and onion.
Remove the mixture from the pan and drain it.
In the same pot, mix the beans, chilies and tomatoes; cook on medium heat until the mixture is cooked down just a little.
Return the possum and onion to the pot.

title: microwave salmon ring
directions: Drain salmon, discarding bones and skin. Flake and set aside. Combine celery, green pepper and onion in a 2-quart glass casserole dish. Cook uncovered in the microwave 2 minutes on high or until tender. Add flaked salmon, bread crumbs, lemon juice and a mixture of the evaporated milk and egg to the vegetables. Mix well. Carefully spoon the salmon mixture into a 5 1/2-6 cup microwave-safe ring mold. Cover with waxed paper.

title: grandmother's special pork chops
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper, then dredge in flour.
Brown on both sides and remove from pan.
Drain grease from skillet, then put chops back in skillet.
Cut lemons in quarters and squeeze juice over chops.
Place lemons on top of chops, along with bell pepper strips and onion rings.
Add water, lemon pepper spice, Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce to cover all.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chops are tender.
This gravy is excellent on mashed potatoes.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Blend ingredients with fork until well mixed and crumbly.

title: baka
directions: Peel and grate potatoes; drain well, then add chopped onions. Fry bacon crisp; crumble into batter.
Plus the bacon fat.
Soak bread in water and squeeze out water.
Crumble into potato batter. Add milk, salt and pepper; bake at 350° for one hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Mix sour cream, parsley, soup and milk.
Peel and slice potatoes and layer in casserole; season with salt and pepper.
Place layer of chops and top with sauce. Repeat with potatoes, chops with sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar in small pan.
Cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until sugar dissolves, remove from heat.
Stir in mustard, ginger and pineapples.
Combine cornstarch and juice; blend well.
Gradually stir into hot mixture (stir constantly) over medium heat until smooth and thick.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 cups.

title: fruit chutney
directions: Mix and cook until thick.

title: dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: night before french toast
directions: The night before, melt butter and brown sugar in a small pan, stirring.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay bread slices on top of brown sugar mix.
Combine eggs with milk and cinnamon. Pour over the bread.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, preheat oven to 350° and uncover baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with syrup, honey or chopped blueberries mixed with 2 tablespoons orange juice.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk, 1/4 cup butter and salt; beat at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth. Spoon into a greased, shallow 2-quart casserole.

title: trappers pepper bean special
directions: Dice onion and green pepper and fry with hamburger.
Drain corn and beans.
Mix all ingredients and simmer.
Thin with milk if desired.
Serve over rice or noodles or eat as a hot dish.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix together last 3 ingredients.
Layer all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Spread salad dressing mixture on top.
Sprinkle with some Cheddar cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: mom's chicken wings
directions: Lightly flour and season with salt and pepper the chicken wings.
Deep fry until lightly brown. Drain. Toss wings in mixture of the Worcestershire sauce, honey and cayenne pepper sauce.
Put in baking dish and bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: summertime relish
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir onions and green peppers in oil over medium heat until onions are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat to boil.
Cool, covered, in refrigerator for several days.
Makes 3 cups.

title: tangy chicken
directions: In large skillet, saute onion, garlic and herbs in olive oil. Stir in tomatoes, catsup, vinegar, bouillon and pepper.
Add chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.

title: cheddar spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on crackers.
Better if make in advance and put in refrigerator.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Then add next 3 ingredients, cutting through cream cheese with fork.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture in a large bowl and chill until set.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Stir with spoon and add nuts. Serve with sliced red or yellow apples. Squeeze lemon on apples to keep from turning dark.

title: apricot cream cheese salad
directions: Bring water, sugar and Jell-O to boil.
Add pineapple and baby food.
Cool and refrigerate until it starts to jell.
Add blended cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken and tear into small pieces. Cook macaroni (or noodles) according to directions.
Mix macaroni, chicken, sour cream, soup, 1/2 can broth and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
(If mixture seems too thick, add more broth.)
Sprinkle top of dish with Parmesan cheese and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: miniature cherry cheesecake
directions: You will also need cupcake liners.

title: cheese and apple spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and miracle whip, mixing until well blended. Add cheese and apples. Mix well. Serve with crackers.

title: cheese cake
directions: Whip cream cheese until light and fluffy to a peak.
Stir in the lemon juice, then stir in milk.
Put in vanilla.
Stir until it is nice and creamy, then put in pie crust.
Chill for 2 hours, then put your cherry pie filling on and chill until you are ready to eat.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Twenty minutes before serving:
In a large kettle over medium heat, heat ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Then add 2 cups orange juice (not necessary).
Drain off spices if you prefer. Serve hot.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Use to bake boneless spareribs or cut boneless pork chops in half.
Pour 1/2 sauce over the meat and bake covered 3 hours at 350°.

title: great snack
directions: Fry hamburger until brown.
Drain fat, then pour hamburger in mixing bowl.
Follow the same for the Italian sausage.
Cut up all of the Velveeta cheese.
Add to hamburger and sausage.
Cut up onions and add to mix.
Microwave until cheese melts, then place spoonfuls on bread and bake until top is crispy.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Mix jelly and mustard.
Melt in crock-pot.
Add sliced smoked sausage.
Cook on low for 1 to 2 hours.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Blend together first 6 ingredients.
Add rest and mix well. Bake in greased and floured pans.
Yields 2 large bread pans/loaves.
If using a Bundt pan, a little will be left over. Freezes well.
Keep in refrigerator in hot weather; molds easily.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Combine sugar and oil; add egg whites and beat at medium speed for 1 minute. Stir in pineapple, carrot, buttermilk, vanilla and raisins.
Add flour mixture and stir well. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool and frost.

title: quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle cheese, broccoli and ham onto pie crust.
Beat eggs and half and half together.
Pour into pie crust while on oven rack.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, oil and egg; mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown and wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: hot romaine potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from drippings and drain on absorbent paper.
Reserve 1/2 cup bacon drippings in frypan.
Add potatoes, celery and green onions; mix.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown rice in oil until a nutty brown.
Add onion; saute until clear.
Add tomatoes (tomatoes should be chopped up to desired bite size), water, bouillon cube, garlic salt, carrots and peas.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook until rice is tender and water is cooked out.
If necessary, add more water and let simmer dry again to get rice tender.
Once you bring rice to boil, never, never stir any more!!
If you do, you will have sticky rice.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Prepare dough for rolled biscuits as directed on box.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll dough onto floured surface and form a 12 x 7-inch rectangle.
Spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle with the mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Add pecans, if desired.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook the molasses, sugar, vanilla, salt and vinegar until a fine string will fall from spoon. Remove from heat and add butter and soda. Stir well and pour over popped corn.
Mix well.
Roll with hands in medium size balls.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 dozen balls.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon on top.
Store tightly in covered container.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook ham shank 1/2 hour; add rest of ingredients and cook for at least 3 hours on low heat.
Serve with cornbread.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
While noodles cook, stir together sour cream, 1/4 cup cheese, chives, salt, pepper and garlic.
Return noodles to kettle and stir in butter.
Fold in sour cream mixture.
Arrange on warm platter.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of cheese.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix salt, milk, vanilla and pudding for 1 minute with mixer. Let set for 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: chili-spaghetti
directions: In saucepan, brown sausage, onions and carrots until tender. Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato juice, kidney beans, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Place uncooked spaghetti in a 1-quart casserole.
Stir in meat mixture.
Bake at 375° about 55 to 60 minutes, stirring twice.
Makes 2 or 3 servings.

title: pineapple papaya salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Season with salt and chill well.

title: mush(my grandmother used to serve us mush for breakfast.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Place in a double boiler and cook 1 hour.
(Watch that the water in bottom of double boiler doesn't go dry.)*
Pour ingredients into a loaf pan and let cool overnight in refrigerator.
When ready, cut into slices and fry in lightly oiled skillet until brown on both sides.

title: baked creamed corn
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat with beater just until creamy.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Stir after 30 minutes.

title: peanut bars
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Add sugar slowly and beat until light.
Add cream, milk, vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Bake in a shallow pan at 375°.
When cool cut into slices, frosting all sides with powdered sugar frosting and roll in chopped peanuts.

title: peanut butter and dill pickle sandwich
directions: Take 2 slices of loaf of bread.
Spread peanut butter on the bread.
Add dill pickle slices on top of the peanut butter.
Put the two sliced pieces of bread together.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Place in large container. Cover tightly.
Place desired amount in cup.
Fill cup with hot water.
Stir well.

title: holiday delight
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 3 ingredients together.
Blend in Cool Whip gently and thoroughly.
Chill at least 3 or 4 hours before serving.
May also be frozen and served like that.
The pale green color makes it a nice treat for the holidays.

title: christmas sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles; wash and cut into chunks.
Put pickle chunks, sugar and spices in jar (in layers).
Stir every day until sugar melts.
Keep in refrigerator.
Ready to eat in 2 weeks.
Good!

title: baked candy
directions: Preheat oven to exactly 250°. Everything used in this preparation should be either glass or metal with no oil deposits at all. Beat egg whites stiff. Blend in light brown sugar and vanilla (this should make a creamy white texture). Hand mix with metal spoon the chopped pecans. On lightly colored baking pan, no sides use either parchment paper or wax paper. Use metal spoon and drop 1-inch apart. Bake only 1 pan at a time for 30 minutes, then turn oven off and let sit in oven for 30 minutes. Refrain from opening oven until completely cooked.

title: cheese cake
directions: Prepare 10-inch graham cracker crust according to directions on box.
Bake.
Beat cheese, eggs and sugar in electric mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Add the remaining ingredients and beat lightly.
Put in baked crust and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool 5 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set in mold or favorite dish for 3 hours.

title: milk shakes
directions: Mix together and shake.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: Blend well; add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken; do not salt.
Pick chicken off bone; set aside. Save broth.
Melt margarine; stir into stuffing mix.
In a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish, layer stuffing mix, onion, chicken pieces and mushroom soup (diluted with 1
can broth).
Layer again the stuffing mix, onion, chicken pieces and chicken soup diluted with can of broth.
Top with stuffing crumbs.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: southwest green chili cornbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well-buttered 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. Add sliced apples. Pour into a 9 x 9 pan and sprinkle with a topping of 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and egg yolk and press into large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: nacho popcorn
directions: In a small bowl, stir paprika, red pepper and cumin into melted margarine.
Gently toss mixture with popcorn to coat evenly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, toss until coated.

title: party potatoes
directions: In large bowl, stir together thawed potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with corn flake crumbs; drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deluxe beef roast
directions: Bake roast in covered roaster at 325 degrees for 3 - 4 hour or until done.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Remove from heat. Add sugar. Stir well. Add eggs one at a time. Add vanilla, flour and chopped nuts. Mix well. Pour mixture into 2 round 9-inch pie pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Let cool. Roll into balls and cover with powdered sugar.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Butter casserole; place cooked noodles, corn, tuna, pepper and soup in alternate layers in dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Place in moderate oven until golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: hot crab souffle(or shrimp or chicken)
directions: Dice 4 slices of bread, with crust, in 9 x 15-inch baking dish.
Mix crab, onion, mayonnaise, green pepper and celery. Spread over diced bread.
Trim crust from remaining bread.
Place the four whole slices over crab mixture.
Beat eggs and milk. Pour over mixture in casserole.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread evenly in greased 8 x 13-inch pan in order listed.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: pretzel mix
directions: Put pretzels in baking pan.
Sprinkle onion soup over pretzels and bake 15 minutes.
Pour 2 sticks melted oleo over pretzels and bake 15 minutes more.
Mix well and store in airtight container. Bake at 250°.

title: toffee treat dessert
directions: Mix flour, salt and brown sugar.
Cut in butter.
Save 1 cup of this mixture.
To remaining mixture, add soda, milk, egg and vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Shave chilled candy bars over top of batter.
Also add crumbs and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and mix.
Combine soda to persimmon pulp and mix into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Add flour mixture and stir.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix together, knead, roll-out, cut in narrow strips.
Lay out to dry.
Drop in boiling broth.
Cook 5-10 minutes, or until tender.

title: strawberry topping for cake
directions: Mix all together and beat on high speed for 20 minutes. Wonderful
on angel food or sponge cake.
Split cake into 3 layers.
Fill with ice cream.
I freeze cake first.
Refreeze until topping is ready.
Ice cake with topping and freeze.
Keep frozen.

title: mashed potato doughnuts
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs and milk.
Sift together baking powder and spices and add to milk mixture.
Add enough of the 5 cups flour to stiffen and mix in mashed potatoes.
Fry in deep fat at high temperature until golden brown.

title: hershey's triple chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In mixer bowl, beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs and milk; beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa and baking soda; gradually add to butter mixture, blending well.
Stir in chocolate chips. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake 10 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute; remove to wire rack.
Press Kisses in center of each cookie.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: squash dressing
directions: Drain and mash cooked squash.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in oleo.
Add to squash.
Crumble cooked cornbread in squash.
Add soup, egg, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in pan and bake 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with grated cheese and bake 15 minutes more.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and cocoa.
Beat eggs and stir in flour, vanilla and Pet milk.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in pie shell.
Makes 3 pies.

title: marshmallow and chocolate popcorn balls
directions: Place popped corn in large greased pan.
Melt marshmallow topping and chocolate bits in top of double boiler.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over popcorn, mixing thoroughly.
Shape into balls.
If desired, place wooden ice cream stick in balls.
Makes about 14.

title: apricot pudding
directions: Saturate the bread crumbs with the juice drained off the stewed fruit (or a little hot water).
Add fruit and the beaten egg yolk to the crumbs.
Stir in sugar.
Beat the egg white until stiff; fold into fruit mixture.
Pour pudding into buttered ramekins (or a glass baking dish).
Bake in a moderate oven (350°).
When nearly done, remove from oven, top with a marshmallow and return to oven until marshmallow is toasted.

title: shirley's spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove whole cloves and whole cinnamon, if used.
Makes 1 gallon and 1 quart.

title: family spinach
directions: Cook spinach until just tender.
Drain very thoroughly.
Add mushroom soup, seasonings, sesame seed and 1/2 nuts.
Turn into buttered 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbly and brown.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together.
Place in a medium bowl.
Top with Cool Whip around the sides of the bowl, leaving the center free of Cool Whip.
Top with cherries if desired or mix with other fruits.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Pour into glass bowl; chill.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain fat.
All remaining ingredients in large pot.
Bring to a boil, stirring often so it won't stick. Lower heat and simmer for 2 hours or put in crock pot and simmer on high all day.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients together and line buttered torte pan leaving 1 cup for top.
Mix well the eggs, sugar, cottage cheese, flour, cream and vanilla.
Pour into crust and cover with the 1 cup of crust mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: dutch potato bread
directions: Peel and dice potatoes; cover with three-inches of water. Cook until tender (saving 2 cups of water).
Mash in rest of liquid or blend in food processor.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes (be sure and check so they will not overcook).
Cool.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Skin and cut lengthwise.
Rinse chicken under running water and pat dry.
Place chicken, bone side up, on the unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Broil chicken to 4 to 5 inches from heat for 15 minutes. Turn.
Continue broiling for 10 minutes.

title: applesauce pancakes(great)
directions: Put all ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Beat ingredients until smooth with a wire whisk.
Pour by 1/4 cupfuls onto hot skillet.
Cook until edges are dry.
Turn; cook until brown. Serve while hot with butter or syrup.

title: no cook ham and cheese rolls
directions: Put cream cheese in microwave oven for one minute.
Then spread thinly on each slice of ham.
After spreading, roll ham into rolls.
Put on plate and freeze for about 30 minutes.
Take out of freezer and slice in small slices and enjoy!

title: bacon-cheese appetizer pie
directions: Roll the pastry into a 13 1/2-inch circle. Fit into the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch spring-form pan. Lightly prick the bottom. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool slightly.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix the melted margarine, 3 tablespoons sugar and crushed pretzels.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: joann bowden's spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Place in covered container.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Heat sauce; serve over spaghetti.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place beef in a 3-quart pan.
Sprinkle with salt, basil and pepper.
Place celery, carrots and onions on top of beef.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over meat and vegetables, making sure all pieces are coated.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Add potatoes and bake 45 minutes longer.
Great for a cold winter day.

title: oven baked hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1 cup of crushed corn flakes or potato chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed;
drain well.
Saute onion in shortening until
clear.
Cook
ground beef until light brown. Combine with
all ingredients and macaroni.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour until slightly brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over medium heat until thick in heavy saucepan or skillet.
Pour into cooled, cooked pie crust and top with meringue.
Brown in medium oven.
This makes two small pies or one deep-dish pie.

title: bean 'n bacon burgers
directions: Cook onion and green peppers in margarine until tender.
Add the beef.
Brown.
Stir to separate meat particles.
Add the soup, water, ketchup, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes to blend flavors.
(Thin to desired consistency with water.)
Cook 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar thoroughly in a large bowl of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.
Combine flour with salt and add alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour. Dissolve soda in boiling water and beat into mixture.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured tube pan and bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours, testing for doneness after 1 1/4 hours.
Let rest 5 to 10 minutes before turning out.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Put a nice layer of crushed chips in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger.
Add the rest of the ingredients, cooking about 10 minutes.
If you use the enchilada mix, you will need 1 can of tomato sauce added, also.
Pour this mixture over the chips.
Top with more chips and the grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl except for chips.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish ungreased.
Sprinkle top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour or until mixture bubbles and top browns.
Good if made the night before and then baked when needed.

title: homemade pizza dough
directions: Put warm water in bowl.
Add yeast, salt, sugar and oil; mix well.
Add flour.
Mix well into a ball.
Grease bowl; put dough in.
Let rise about 20 minutes.
Pat out on 2 greased pizza pans or 1 cookie sheet.
Add favorite sauce and toppings.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt margarine and add to rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: john's salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornstarch, in a large pot.
Heat to boiling point.
Remove 1 cup mix and add cornstarch to it. Stir well and return to pot.
Stir and cook only until cornstarch is dissolved.
Take from heat.
Cool.
Store in jars in refrigerator for 10 days to two weeks.

title: spaghetti and chopped bologna
directions: Combine the onion
and green pepper in a pot; saute for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over a low fire until hot, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mom's shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients using enough mayonnaise to reach firm, but spreadable consistency. Double recipe for large crowd.

title: candy-stripe twists
directions: Measure flour, baking powder and salt into sifter.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar until fluffy in large bowl.
Beat in egg and oil of anise.
Sift in dry ingredients, a third at a time, adding alternately with milk; stir until well blended.
Spoon half of dough into a medium-size bowl; blend in a few drops red food coloring to tint pink.
Leave other half plain.
Pinch off about a teaspoonful each of pink and white dough at a time and roll each into a pencil-thin strip, about 5-inches long on lightly floured pastry cloth or board.
Place strips, side by side, pressing ends together, then twist into a rope.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes or until firm.
Remove carefully from cookie sheets; cool on wire racks.
Store with waxed paper or transparent wrap between layers in container with tight-fitting cover.

title: sunday night casserole
directions: Use 3-quart casserole dish or 2 (11-inch) casseroles.
Layer as follows:
1/2 of the bread, 1/2 of the sausage, 1/2 of the grated cheese and repeat.

title: delicious drop cookies
directions: Cream oleo, oil, egg, brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Combine these and add oatmeal and Rice Krispies.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Mix ice cream and strawberries.
Put mixture into punch bowl. Add juice and ginger ale.
Serves 25.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread blueberry pie filling in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle lemon juice over pie filling.
Combine butter, nuts and cake mix. Mixture will be crumbly.
Sprinkle this mix over top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° (or until brown).
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Make Jiffy cake in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish according to directions. Cool. Mix the cream cheese, instant pudding and milk; spread over cake. Spread drained crushed pineapple over cheese mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries. Chill 2 hours.

title: baked bananas
directions: Peel bananas; split lengthwise and cut crosswise into halves. Place in greased 5 x 10-inch Pyrex dish.
Peel orange; cut in sections and place in small bowl with honey and lemon juice.
Toss lightly and spoon over bananas.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bananas are soft.
Remove bananas from pan with spatula to prevent breaking.
Sprinkle with coconut and place a maraschino cherry on each serving.
Serves 8.

title: mother's pear relish
directions: Grind everything - grind pears first and put in sieve and let drain while you grind peppers and onions.
Put on stove and cook 30 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: judy's sour cream pecan pound cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well and beat about 3 minutes.
In another bowl, combine the last 3 ingredients.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan or tube pan.
Sprinkle approximately 1/3 of cinnamon mixture in bottom of pan; add 1/3 of batter.
Repeat two more times, ending with batter.
Run a knife through to marbleize. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp ala creole
directions: Clean shrimp and boil 5 minutes, saving stock.

title: ham 'n' biscuit skillet(preparation time:  20 minutes)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Peel onion and cut in thin wedges.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes until just tender. Add tomatoes and frozen greens.
Cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes until greens are thawed.
Drain beans and cut ham in bite size pieces.
Stir ham, beans, and ketchup into skillet.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat and arrange biscuits, just touching, in a ring around edge of skillet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until biscuits are golden brown on top and fully cooked on bottom (lift one to check).
Yields 4 servings.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix peanut butter, melted butter, powdered sugar, brown sugar and vanilla together in large bowl.
Put 1/2-inch thick on cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over.
Cut while warm.

title: chocolate tater fudge
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine potato and water.
Cook on High in microwave until soft.
Drain.
Mash potato with milk; set aside.

title: nutty loaf
directions: Saute onions and celery in oil until tender.
Finely grind almonds or liquify with water in blender until very fine.
Combine all ingredients, except gravy.
Pack into greased loaf pan or ring mold.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with mushroom gravy.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix beef consomme, water, onion soup mix and mushrooms.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cut up margarine on top.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: lemon park avenue squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, nuts and margarine. Put in 9 x 12 pan and press down. Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla or lemon flavoring. Spread this on top of cake in pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: wheat germ patties
directions: Mix ingredients all together and form into patties.
Brown in oil.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in 24 x 18 x 4-inch pan.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add flour, then pineapple.
Beat eggs and bake at 350° until done.

title: beef roast
directions: Mix flour and soup mix together.
Place meat into roaster or ovenproof pan.
Put salt and pepper on roast.
Pour flour/soup mix over roast.
Cook at 350° for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Potatoes and carrots can be added the last 30 minutes.
I prefer to cook my potatoes and carrots separately.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage in medium skillet until browned; drain.
Set aside.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles; place triangles with elongated points toward center in a greased 12-inch pizza pan. Press bottom and sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over dough; sprinkle with hash browns and Cheddar cheese. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over sausage mixture. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional cheese.
tags: frozen loosely packed hash brown potatoes

title: rice and broccoli hot dish
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake.
Stir twice while baking.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Use 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Serves 4 to 8.

title: murel's cookies
directions: Butter electric frypan.
Melt chocolate in pan.
Beat eggs, salt and sugar together and add with dates to chocolate, stirring constantly.
Cook for 10 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan or heat.
Add nuts, vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls into coconut.
Roll into balls and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients and pack firmly into a greased large loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take out and pour 1/2 cup of ketchup over top of the loaf.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Take out and let stand for about 5 minutes before slicing.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Saute onions, garlic and bell pepper in margarine. Cook until onions are translucent.

Add 1/4 cup flour to vegetables. Cover and cook on low 15 minutes. Add crawfish and parsley to vegetables and cook 15 more minutes. Stir in Velveeta and half and half. When thoroughly blended, add boiled fettucine. Bake in covered dish at 350° for 15 minutes. Can also serve sauce over fettucine instead of casserole-style.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix altogether and bake at 350° until cake springs back when touched.

title: pistachio fluff
directions: Take a large bowl and put pistachio pudding mix in.
Blend in a can of chopped pineapple, Cool Whip and mini marshmallows. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with roll of crushed Ritz crackers and slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock pot beef barley soup
directions: Brown the Stew Beef in hot Oil.
Drain.
In cooker, combine Carrots, Celery, Onion, Green Pepper, and Parsley.
Add Broth, undrained chopped Tomatoes.
Spaghetti Sauce, Barley, Basil, Salt and Pepper.
Stir in browned meat.
Slow cooker on low for 10-12 hours or on high for 4-5 hours.

title: spicy pork rub
directions: Combine ingredients and rub over entire surface of meat.
You can cook immediately or refrigerate overnight.
The longer the herbs are on meat, the more intense the flavor.
Cook pork using your favorite method.
Very tasty!

title: hungarian chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice.
Brown in butter in frying pan.
Put chicken in shallow baking dish.
Add onion to pan drippings; fry until done.
Combine soup, paprika, sour cream, salt and pepper; add to onion.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Boil sugar, 1 cup water and oleo for 5 minutes.
Make a batter of flour, yolks and milk.
Add to sugar syrup.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into ready baked pie shell.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except for eggs and vanilla.
Cook until mixture is hot.
Add small amount to beaten egg yolks.
Add egg yolks then to rest of mixture; cook until thick.
Add vanilla and pour into baked pie shell.
Makes one pie.
Use egg whites for meringue or use Cool Whip.

title: confetti salad
directions: Drain all the canned vegetables.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep several days.

title: country cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage, pepper and onion.
Set aside.
Mix together vinegar, water, salad dressing or oil, sugar and salt.
Pour over cabbage mixture.

title: turkey or chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in turkey broth according to directions on box. Combine spaghetti and all other ingredients; mix together well. Place in two-quart casserole dish and top with grated cheese. Bake in oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
(Can be prepared ahead and frozen.)

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Break white bread into small crumbs; wet and squeeze damp. Mix into ground beef; add the sour cream, onions, salt, pepper and water.
Form into balls and roll on bread crumbs.
Brown in skillet in butter for 10 minutes.
When done, remove the meat balls from skillet and make a gravy.
Place meat balls into gravy.

title: no knead bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add other ingredients; mix well. Make into cloverleaf rolls or loaves.
Let rise only 1 time.
Will keep in refrigerator, covered with foil, for a week.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: recipe for a happy day
directions: Mix all the ingredients with Prayer and serve in generous portions.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix flour with salt and cocoa; put soda in buttermilk.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and buttermilk alternately. Add vanilla, chips and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: year round cranberry salad
directions: Heat water and 1 cup of orange juice to boiling. Dissolve jello and salt in boiling liquid in mixing/serving bowl. Stir in the remaining orange juice. Place in refrigerator to cool until the consistency of egg whites. Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple, celery and nuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: flower pot dirt cake
directions: In a food processor or blender, crush cookies until fine.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, butter and sugar until smooth.
In another bowl, mix pudding and milk until well blended.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Add lemon juice and salt to mayonnaise. Mix well with cream cheese. Add nuts, quartered cherries and pineapple.
Stir well to blend.
Add well beaten whipped cream
and fold in.
Add bananas, cut in small chunks. Put in freezer tray and freeze.

title: walnut raisin apple cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar until crumbly. Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Add apple juice and lemon extract. Combine the flour, soda, salt, oats, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Gradually add to the creamed mixture. Stir in the apples, raisins and nuts. Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet 2-inches apart. Bake in 350° oven for 11 to 13 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: raisin molasses gems
directions: Beat shortening and 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy. Add molasses and egg; beat well.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: To cook carrots: heat lightly salted water to boil; add carrots and return to boil. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 10-12 minutes until crisp and tender. Drain well; return carrots to pan. Stir in marmalade, butter, mustard and ginger. Simmer uncovered over medium heat 3 minutes or until carrots are glazed, stirring occasionally.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Sprinkle with turmeric.
Dissolve salt in 2 quarts cold water and pour over vegetables.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag; add to sugar and vinegar.
Heat to boiling and pour over vegetables.
Cover and let stand 12 to 18 hours in cold place.
Simmer until hot. Bring to boiling.
Pack into jars, leaving 1/8-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll in nuts and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture. Chill dough for about 1 hour before baking.
Keep dough chilled between baking batches.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls and place 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork if desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in cherries and almond extract.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute after mixture starts to thicken.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut shortening into flour, sugar, baking powder and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk.
Drop dough by 6 spoonfuls onto hot cherry mixture.
Bake until dough is golden brown.
Bake at 400° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Great with vanilla ice cream.

title: pineapple cookies(low calorie)
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 16 cookies.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together.
Just before serving, add oil and vinegar dressing of your choice.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine Ricotta and sour cream in a mixing bowl. Beating slowly, add cream cheese, sugar and butter. Increase speed to medium and add eggs, flour, cornstarch, vanilla and lemon juice. Beat on highest speed possible without splatting for 5 more minutes. Pour mixture into 10-inch spring-form pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Turn heat off and leave in oven for 1 hour; let cool.

title: poppy seed egg noodles
directions: In a large pot, bring water and salt to a boil. Add noodles and cook, uncovered, until al dente (4 to 8 minutes, depending on size). Drain. Melt butter in pot in which noodles were cooked. Return noodles to pot and add poppy seed, tossing gently to mix. Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil,
eggs	and sugar and add the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in apples and chopped nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased	and
floured
pan.
Sprinkle
butterscotch morsels on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, cream peanut butter, shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda; gradually add to creamed mixture, blending thoroughly.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; immediately place unwrapped peanut butter cup on top of each cookie, pressing down so that cookie cracks around edges.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: seafood americaine(yields 4 servings)
directions: Butter 4 ramekins.
In a saucepan melt margarine.
Stir in onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is clear and yellow, not brown. Remove garlic and discard.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add chicken stock.
Cook until thickened.
Add tomato paste, wine and seasonings.
Remove from heat.
Stir in desired seafood, cut in small pieces.
Turn into ramekins.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Before baking, sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Garnish with lemon slice and parsley sprig.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in lightly salted water until done.
Bone and cut chicken into small pieces.
Save the broth.
Melt margarine and mix well with the package of stuffing.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Add all ingredients together and pour into a slightly prebaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.
Serve chilled with any fruit wedges or can also be used to frost muffins.

title: pickled okra sandwiches
directions: Remove crust from bread. Roll with rolling pin until thin. Coat each slice with cream cheese. Place okra spear in center. Roll up and spread thin layer of cream cheese on the outside, then roll in chopped parsley. You can slice them in small slices or in half.

title: tangy tomato sauce
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour in buttermilk all at once and immediately stir vigorously over moderate heat until thickened.
Add chili sauce and mix well. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: ma vivian's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well and let set while making pie crust.
Pour into three 9-inch pie crusts.
Bake 15 minutes on 400° and then turn oven back to 350° and finish baking (about 55 minutes).

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, corn syrup, eggs, vanilla, butter and salt. Add pecans.
Bake in unbaked 9-inch pie shell or 8 tart shells. Bake at 250° for 1 hour for pie, 40 minutes for tart shells.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Spread this mixture evenly over batter; pour boiling water over all.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover dish with foil during the last half hour. Serve with whipped cream.

title: "frisco" tuna
directions: Cook noodles as package directs.
Drain off water and add oil. Saute onions.
Combine tomato, onions, salts, pepper and parsley. In a casserole place half the noodles, then half the tuna, then half the cheese slices.
Pour on half tomato mixture.
Repeat. Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: new zealand bacon and egg pie
directions: Place one pastry in pie pan.
Place enough chopped onion or onion flakes in bottom of pan to taste.
Cube ham slices and sprinkle over onion.
Beat eggs with milk and pepper.
Pour over ham and onion.
Place 4 slices of cheese on top.
Add pastry top. Edge as you would any pie.
Smooth any remaining egg over pastry top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix soda with sour cream (set aside).
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and stir.
Mix sour cream with dry ingredients and alternate with butter and sugar.
Beat 2 minutes. Bake in 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: nana's coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Add 1 package coconut to cake batter.
Blend well.
Bake according to directions and cool. Punch holes in top with fork.
Open can of Coco Lopez and fill space to top with milk.
Mix well and pour over cake.
When cake is cold spread 12 ounces of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
Peel potatoes and put in heavy skillet with melted margarine; add white sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Cook until it comes to a boil; boil about 15 minutes on low to medium heat.
Put in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, cheese, sour cream and soup.
Add pepper, parsley flakes and paprika.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix corn flakes with 1 stick melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain each can of beans, peas and corn.
Put the onion, celery and green pepper in a bowl.
Heat the sugar, vinegar and oil.
When cool, pour over vegetables and add chopped pimentos for color.

title: buster bars
directions: Mix crushed cookies and butter together.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze 1 hour.
Let ice cream soften a little.
Press it over crumbs.
Sprinkle and press peanuts into ice cream.
Freeze again.

title: banana split pudding(8 to 10 servings)
directions: To reserved pineapple liquid add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.

title: millionaire pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix altogether.
Put in 9-inch pie shells already baked.
Put in icebox or freeze.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix oleo, shortening, water and cocoa and bring to a boil. Pour into large mixing bowl and add sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, cinnamon, salt, buttermilk and soda; mix well.
Bake on cookie sheet with sides at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter with brown sugar.
Add flour and mix until crumbly.
Press into an oblong pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: burrito bake
directions: In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain. Add the beans, onion and taco seasoning. Unroll crescent roll dough. Press onto the bottom and up the sides of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Seal seams and perforations. Spread beef mixture over crust. Sprinkle with cheeses. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Sprinkle with toppings of your choice: chopped lettuce, tomatoes, ripe olives, etc. Yield: 6 servings.

title: rice-a-roni
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as on package; cool.
Cook carrots 5 minutes or until tender, but not soft.
Cool.
After cooked ingredients have cooled, mix all together with 1/2 cup mayonnaise; chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: On split English muffins, spread some Ragu sauce; add your desired toppings and cheeses.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes. You can choose your own toppings.
A great slumber party dish where each child can make his or her own pizza.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until almost done.
Add egg noodles. Cook until done.
Add cheese.
Let melt.
Add milk and heat (do not boil).
Serve.

title: cauliflower frittata(frittata di cavolfiore)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut cauliflower into florets and cook in
boiling salted water for 5 to 8 minutes.
In skillet heat
oil and saute onions until slightly golden.
Add drained cauliflower, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on medium
heat. Beat
eggs and milk in a bowl with the Parmesan cheese
and
set mix with cauliflower mixture.
Grease 8-inch baking dish
with butter
and
pour
cauliflower mixture into dish.
Bake for approximately
35 to 45 minutes or until eggs feel set and
firm. To serve, sprinkle with a little Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
A great luncheon or sidedish.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Coat pan sides with butter.
Pour ingredients into pan and bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes. Great with syrup.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and cold water; beat well.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Put in greased cookie sheet; sprinkle chocolate chips on top.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel apples.
Slice apples and put in a glass baking pan.
Mix flour, butter and sugar.
Spread over top of the apples.
Make a hole in the middle of the apples and mixture.
Pour in hot water.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add the sugar gradually.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; continue to beat.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour; measure and sift again with cocoa and salt.
Add alternately with sour milk.
Add soda to boiling water.
When dissolved, add all at once to mixture.
Stir only enough to blend ingredients.
This makes a very thin batter.
Pour immediately into greased layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes two (8-inch) layers.
Very moist.

title: queso relleno(stuffed cheese)
directions: Oil a casserole dish.
Put Mozzarella cheese on the bottom. In skillet, cook pork with onion and garlic until meat is brown. Drain off fat.
Stir in half the undrained tomatoes, salt, oregano, pepper, allspice and cinnamon.
Simmer, covered, for 2 minutes.
Put hot meat mixture over Mozzarella and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven about 10 minutes.

title: chef salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar; shake well to mix.
Yield 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until dissolved.
Then boil in microwave for 2 minutes.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell. Refrigerate.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple until pudding is moist.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Cut pound cake into thirds, longways.
Put a layer of Cool Whip mixture in between each layer of pound cake. Top with another layer of Cool Whip mixture.
Can garnish with sliced almonds.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.

title: fresh peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 10-inch square pan or 13 x 9-inch. Sprinkle with brown sugar on top.
Arrange pecan halves and fresh peach slices attractively on butter-sugar mixture.
Pour cake mix over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Invert pan onto platter.
Serve warm with whipped cream and dust of nutmeg.

title: sausages and rappi
directions: Fry sausages in open frypan until almost cooked.
Remove and set aside.
Add garlic and almost brown. Return sausages to pan and add rappi (washed and drained).
Cover and cook rappi until tender; stir often.
Salt and pepper added during cooking rappi. Serve hot with crusty Italian bread and red wine.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in greased baking pan.
Mix together the next three ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Do not cover.
Baste or turn halfway through baking time.

title: baba ghanouj ii
directions: Grill eggplant on top of stove on low heat for 15 minutes or put in oven on 350° for 45-60 minutes, or until eggplant is soft. In a blender, put cumin, lemon juice, salt green chili, 3 Tbsp. olive oil, tahineh, garlic, parsley, and water.
Blend until smooth.
After grilling the eggplant, peel it and wash.
Mash it with a fork and mix it with the blender mixture completely.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Do not strain.

title: bright green beans
directions: Take your nonstick frying pan and spread the frozen beans over the bottom.
Add broth and onions and simmer over low heat until liquid evaporates.
Stir often so that beans cook evenly.
Don't cover the pan; beans cooked in a covered pan quickly lose their color and end up a sickly gray-green.
Beans should be crisp and tender by the time the water disappears.
If not cooked sufficiently, add a little more broth, but take care not to overcook.
Don't throw away the pan juices that remain; serve them over the beans.
Serves 3.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix in order given; batter will be thin.
Spoon or pour onto hot griddle or frying pan.
It is not necessary to grease griddle. Turn once; they cook quickly to a light golden color.
They may be kept warm on a platter in a warm oven until all batter is used. Serve with syrup, jam, or fresh fruit.
Serves 2-4 people.
Recipe may be doubled or tripled.
(You will need more frying pans.) Leftovers are good reheated in the microwave.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Combine
Jell-O, water, strawberries and pineapple in a bowl. Let
thicken and then add bananas.	Pour 1/2 of mixture into cold Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate.
When thick and firm, pour whole carton of sour cream on top of Jell-O and spread evenly. Pour
other half
of Jell-O mixture on top.
Serve with salad dressing or whipped cream.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Put all ingredients in double boiler.
Beat with mixture over high heat about 7 minutes or until it fluffs in peaks.

title: rita tibbett's fish(microwave recipe)
directions: Melt
the
butter.
Add
the
lemon
juice.
Add enough cornstarch	to
make
it
feel like cream.	Salt and pepper to individual	tastes.
Roll
haddock	on
both
sides.
Sprinkle parsley
on top and cover with Saran Wrap (microwavable wrap). Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes.	Let it set still, covered, for another 5 minutes.	Very good and a fast meal.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all
ingredients
with 1 cup sour cream (8 ounces). Allow to sit in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours and then serve.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cook rhubarb and sugar until mushy.
While hot, add marshmallows and jello.
Cool thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Makes two pies.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Roll into small balls and bake at 350° for 5 to 20 minutes. Remove from pan and roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: fettuccine with spinach
directions: Cook pasta according to directions, Meanwhile, in large skillet, melt butter. Add onion, garlic and paprika; cook until tender. Add spinach and beef broth; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat simmer for 3 min. Stir flour into sour cream.
Remove pan from heat; stir in sour cream mixture. Toss drained pasta with sauce; serve at once.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: First brown ground beef with diced onions together in skillet.
Put beef and onions in roaster and add soup, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, red hot sauce, celery and add salt and pepper.

title: hot cheese
directions: Grate cheese.
Alternate layers of chilies and cheese in baking dish.
Beat eggs, flour and milk together and pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool a little before cutting in squares.

title: 6-cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; cool and refrigerate until chilled.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Heat oil.
Stir-fry chicken until white.
Season with salt. Add pepper and pineapple syrup.
Boil 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce, vinegar and water and stir in mixture.
Cook until thick.
Stir in pineapple and vegetables and heat.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.
Serve with rice.

title: pumpple butter
directions: Combine ingredients and cook over low heat 4 to 5 hours or until desired thickness.
Keep refrigerated.
The amount of sugar to be used depends on whether using sweetened or unsweetened applesauce.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Chop apples and pecans; set aside.
Mix oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Add chopped apples, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well. Bake in greased and floured 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Stir thoroughly.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
If you add 1 egg, the cake will still be good the next day.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to directions and drain thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pinch off and roll into bite-sized balls.
Freeze.

title: flaky buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Stir in buttermilk just until moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth (1 minute).
Roll out dough to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 8 (2-inch) biscuits; place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: best baked beans ever
directions: Heat oil in skillet until warmed.
Add the onions and saute until tender.
Drain onions.
Combine onions with remaining ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased casserole; chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: australian beef stew
directions: Cut meat into small chunks.
Cut up bacon and fry with diced-up onion.
Add meat; brown well.
Add salt, pepper, marjoram, crushed garlic and wine.
Bring mixture to a boil, lower heat, cover and simmer for an hour.

title: sausage bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

In 10-inch skillet, heat 2 teaspoons oil; add sausage, onions, bell peppers and garlic and cook, breaking up large pieces of sausage with a wooden spoon, until sausage is crumbly and no longer pink and vegetables are soft, about 2 to 3 minutes.
If desired, stir in fennel; stir in salt and pepper.
Set aside and let cool.
On work surface, press pizza dough into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread sausage mixture over entire surface of dough, pressing mixture into dough.

Starting from side end, roll dough jellyroll fashion to enclose filling; pinch each narrow end to seal and tuck ends underneath loaf. Transfer loaf, seam side down, to 9 x 5 x 3-inch nonstick loaf pan and bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Using pastry brush, brush remaining 1/2 teaspoon oil over bread and bake 5 minutes longer.
Remove pan from oven and let cool for 5 minutes. To serve, cut into 10 equal slices.
Serves 10.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly brown ground beef; drain fat. Add mushrooms, chopped onion and bell pepper to ground beef. Brown until vegetables are hot.
Put in casserole dish with both cheeses and cream of mushroom soup; mix well.
Cover casserole thoroughly with Tater Tots (line neatly).
Completely cover with golden mushroom soup (spread evenly).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: chocolate kahlua mousse(delicious and absolutely not calorie free)
directions: Melt chocolate in Kahlua and orange juice over low heat; set aside.
Put egg yolks and eggs in blender with vanilla and sugar, blend well.
Add heavy cream and blend for 30 seconds.
Add chocolate mixture and blend smooth.
Pour into serving dishes. When ready to serve, decorate with whipped cream.
Use pastry bag and star tip to decorate.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Mix wet ingredients, then dry, then altogether.
Drop nuts and chips on top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased loaf pan.
Set pan in hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
To serve, pour over sauce made of 1 can of cream of mushroom soup diluted with 1/3 cup of milk.

title: no knead wheat bread
directions: Heat milk until bubbles form and remove from heat.
Add honey, oil and salt.
Dissolve yeast in large mixing bowl.
Stir in milk with honey, oil and salt along with eggs.
Add 3 white flour and 1 cup whole wheat flour.
Beat on low.
Then beat on medium until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Add 2 cups whole wheat flour with wooden spoon.

title: reuben casserole ii
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer hash browns, then sauerkraut and then corned beef and top with Swiss cheese.	Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cut into squares and top with Thousand Island or Russian dressing.
May add dressing while eating.

title: mushroom logs
directions: Pinch crescent rolls together to make 8 rectangles. Mix cheese, mushrooms and salt.
Spread on rolls.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Cut in 1-inch slices.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Brush beaten egg on top.
Sprinkle on poppy seed, if desired. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: vegetable risotto(low calorie and low cholesterol)
directions: Cook onion
and
rice
in
the	2
tablespoons oil over medium heat
until
golden,
stirring
constantly.
Add green pepper and mushrooms	and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in the frozen corn and the bouillon
or broth.
Bring to boil; stir once or twice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender
and liquid
is	absorbed.
Toss lightly with fork. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
You can add leftover cut up chicken and water chestnuts (if desired) for a main
dish.	You can
also
add
any
combination
of
herbs: rosemary, parsley, basil or marjoram.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook prepared potatoes and carrots until tender.
Drain and retain liquid for gravy.
Saute onion in butter until tender. Blend in flour and salt.
Add broth all at once and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add remaining chicken, peas, potatoes and carrots.
If needed, add more liquid from potatoes and thicken with flour (small amount of flour in cup and slowly add cold water until a paste).
Stir into hot liquid and it will not lump.
Cook pastry according to directions and serve separately or on top of pot pie.
Serves approximately 4 to 6.

title: gooey-butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate. Roll in balls, then in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool. Roll in powdered sugar again.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine bacon, broccoli and onion.
In a separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over the broccoli mix and stir well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator and serve cold. Serves 6 to 8.
Great for summer parties.

title: stars and stripes cake
directions: Line bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish with the pound cake. Top with 1 cup of each of the blueberries and strawberries, then top with the thawed Cool Whip.
Design the "stars and stripes" with the 3 cups halved strawberries and 1/3 cup blueberries. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Makes 15 servings.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Place all ingredients in covered casserole at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and eggs; stir by hand until thoroughly moistened.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness with bottom of glass dipped in flour.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are light brown. Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet.
If you want, spread any kind of frosting on cookies.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: mostaccioli and sausage
directions: In large saucepan, brown sausage and pour off fat.
Add onion and green pepper; cook and stir until tender.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Toss hot, cooked mostaccioli with oil to coat. Serve with sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar and set aside.
Beat eggs lightly; add oil and vanilla and beat 1 minute.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with the apples.
Stir in the walnuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
May frost with a lemon frosting or serve with whipped cream.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Make dressing of sour cream, vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add to cucumbers and chill.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in Pyrex bowl.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts to the mixture.
Microwave on High for 4 1/2 minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes. Add soda.
Stir and pour onto Teflon or greased cookie sheet. Break into pieces when cool.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Place ham on bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle cheese and onion on top of ham.

title: baked beef loaf
directions: Lightly beat eggs in large bowl.
Pour in milk.
Stir in soup, onion, mustard and Worcestershire sauce and crumbs.
Let set a few minutes until crumbs are soaked.
Add ground beef and mix very well.
Place bacon slices over top of meat in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Beat brown sugar and oleo

together; add egg, vanilla and milk. Sift flour, soda and salt; add to mixture. Add rhubarb. Put in greased 9 x 13 pan. Top with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: louise's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; continue to beat.
Add the chocolate, salt, flour, marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Add the vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch square greased and floured baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
The center will be quite moist.
Put on wire rack to cool.
Makes 9 (3-inch) squares or 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until the syrup is hard when tested in cool water (hard crack stage).
I usually tap it on the side of the cup I am testing it in.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain thoroughly.
Place all ingredients in a slow cooker on medium setting.
Stir periodically.
When cheese is melted and all ingredients blended, dip is ready.
Serve with chips.

title: boston baked rice and beans
directions: In
skillet,
cook bacon until about half done.
Remove bacon and drain all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Add onions and cook until
soft,
not
browned.
Add
remaining ingredients. Pour into
a greased 2 quart casserole.	Arrange bacon strips on top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: batter for french fried vegetables
directions: Beat just until well moistened.
Dip vegetables in batter.
Fry a few at a time.
Stir once to separate.
Drain on paper towels. Salt to taste if needed.
Vegetables suggested are:
okra, summer squash, yellow squash, zucchini, or anything you want to experiment with.

title: amaretto souffle
directions: Beat eggs, yolks and sugar for 12 minutes at highest speed. Reduce speed and add Amaretto, fold in crushed macaroons and whipped cream.
Pour into 2-quart souffle dish.
Chill.

title: pickled coleslaw
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the cabbage, green pepper, onion, sugar and carrots.
Boil together the vinegar, oil and salt.
Pour over cabbage mixture and mix well.
Marinate a few hours.

title: short-cut chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; debone and cut up.
Reserve 1 cup of broth; set aside.
Boil noodles as directed.
