In a saucepan, combine cooked noodles, chicken, cheese, hot sauce and broth.
Heat on low until cheese is melted.

title: sauce for sunshine stir-fry(low-fat)
directions: Combine sauce ingredients.
Pour into skillet along with green onions.
Toss until ingredients are mixed and heated through.

title: sugar-free strawberry jam
directions: In a saucepan, bring to a boil the soda.
Remove from heat. Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into jars or plastic containers.
Cover and refrigerate up to 3 weeks. Do not freeze.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Brown pork chops, then add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour until fork-tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put dry rice in shallow baking pan with melted butter on top. Pour over this the can of chicken broth.
Close tightly and leave for 1 hour.
At end of 1 hour, lay chicken on the top of the rice and pour over this the can of cream of celery soup diluted with 1/2 can water.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dorcus' sausage cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix with other ingredients.
Form into large ball.
Wrap in wax paper.
Let sit 1 to 2 hours.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° until brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in microwave-safe dish.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Remove; stir and test squash for tenderness. May need to microwave an additional 5 minutes.

title: pastry
directions: Add eggs, vinegar and water together.
Cut with pastry blender.
Roll out between wax paper.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let sit overnight or at least 2 hours.
Great for veggies.

title: pizza ole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, brown ground beef over medium heat; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning; spoon mixture evenly over baked crust.
Combine eggs, green pepper and onions; pour over meat.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of shredded cheese.
Spoon on salsa and add remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Slice and enjoy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well; put in baking dish.
Add topping.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix; store in a closed container to keep dry.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix the flour and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add milk slowly, then add vanilla.
After mixing all up, add 7 ounce can or package of coconut. Pour into 10-inch pie plate and cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix. Add jalapenos according to how hot your taste buds will stand.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add by small amounts.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken breasts out to 1/4-inch thick.
Wrap each breast around 1 slice of ham and slice of cheese.
Secure ends with a toothpick.
Roll each secured chicken breast in potato chips.
In skillet, lightly brown in butter.
Place in a casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream, sherry and mushrooms.
Pour sauce over chicken, cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Beat other ingredients together; pour fruit on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, add whole cranberry sauce, crushed pineapple, pecans and celery.
Pour in large Pyrex dish and gel.

title: ziegler goulash
directions: Dice green peppers. Cover with water and boil until tender, approximately 15 minutes. Drain. Add drained chopped tomatoes. Add beef (torn into strips).
Heat through. Add cheese and heat over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve on hamburger buns or on toasted bread.

title: boneless swiss steak
directions: Put oil in frying pan.
Let oil get hot.
Just put steak in oil until steak gets light brown on both sides.
Put steak and oil in baking pan, then add 2 1/2 cups water, Lipton onion soup mix and 1 can of soup.
Put top on.
Cook at 350° for about 2 1/2 hours.
If it gets dry, add a can of soup.
When done, take out meat and mix the sauce.
Put on potatoes.

title: onion chowder
directions: Soak potatoes and onions in water as directed on their packages, several hours in advance.
Brown the pork on bottom of kettle until most of the grease is fried out.
Then add potatoes and onions. Cook 10 minutes.
Put in water and milk.
Just before chowder comes to a boil, season with salt and plenty of black pepper.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: easy breakfast donuts
directions: Heat 1/4-inch oil in skillet on stove top on medium-low.
Open the roll of muffins and poke a hole in the center of each one with a knife.
This will give them the shape of a donut.
Place them in the skillet and brown each side until they are fully cooked.
Have bowls of assorted sugars ready and roll the donuts in the sugar as soon as they come out of the skillet.
Best if served warm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Sift half the dry ingredients into sugar mixture.
Blend.
Sift remaining dry ingredients alternately with eggs, one at a time, into mixture, mixing well each time.
Add carrots and mix well.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix in mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour in Bundt pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: down home barbecue sauce(diabetic recipe)
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: fancy fruits
directions: Peel peaches and slice into bowl.
Add strawberries and blueberries.
Sprinkle with sugar as desired.
Sprinkle with liqueur.
Let stand 1 hour.
Just before serving, slice banana into fruit mixture.
Spoon into dessert glasses.
Blend pudding and milk; pour over fruit.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until limp and easy to roll, but not mushy.
Cook rice.
Mix raw ground beef with rice.
Season with salt and pepper. Use large cabbage leaf.
Roll ground beef and rice mixture in cabbage as a blanket, tucking in sides.
In large saucepan, pour tomato juice and add raw bacon strips.
Add stuffed cabbage.
Cook on medium heat 2 1/2 hours.

title: fresh berry cooler
directions: Combine one-third of the berries and 3/4 cup apple juice concentrate in a blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth. Pour into large pitcher and slowly stir in 1 2/3 cups carbonated water.
Repeat twice with remaining ingredients.
Makes 12 servings.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites with salt and vanilla until stiff.
Gradually add sugar until stiff peaks form.
Fold in coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: easy tuna noodle
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
T op with cheese. Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add egg yolks 1 at a time. Beat egg whites until very stiff (set aside). Combine flour and baking powder. Add flour mixture with milk and mix well. Add vanilla and nutmeg. Fold in egg whites with rubber spatula gently but firmly. Pour into a greased 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake is done.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Blend soups and broth (part milk can be used).
Stir in processed cheese.
Mix with spaghetti, turkey and mushrooms.
Pour into greased, shallow baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly and browned for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: a cake mix
directions: This is the first cake I learned to bake at the age of 8 years old.

title: sausage bean meal
directions: Saute the onion, green pepper and sausage.
Mix in casserole the beans, catsup, mustard and sugar.
Add sauteed mixture and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tacos(makes 16)
directions: Brown well and chop up the ground beef; add catsup and chili. Fry tortillas to desired stiffness.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

Generously grease four baking pans. Stir flour, baking soda and salt in a medium bowl; set aside. Beat sugar, oil and eggs in a large mixing bowl until blended. Add bananas and beat until well blended.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture just until moistened.
Stir in chocolate chips. Pour into baking pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then remove.

title: chip and chili pie(good for potluck)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pimento, green chiles and green onion.
Crush 4 cups of chips to make about 2 to 2 1/2 cups.
Reserve 1 cup.
Line bottom of baking dish with half the crushed chips.
Carefully spread half the chili over chips.
Layer half the cheese (pressing down slightly) and half the onion mixture.
Repeat layers.
Garnish with remaining corn chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no fat salad
directions: Mix greens and vegetables together.
Add lemon juice and salt. Cover and set in refrigerator for 5 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix in order given, using 1 cup cheese in mix and 1 cup on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bake in iron skillet or teflon pan.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups butter and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine orange and pineapple juices, sugar, egg and 1 tablespoon of lemon juice. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and cool completely. When cool, fold in the whipped cream. In a large serving bowl, toss apples with remaining lemon juice. Add the bananas and grapes. Add the whipped cream mixture and stir to coat; refrigerate. Fold in pecans just before serving. Yields 20 servings.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Divide eggs.
Use yolks in batter.
Beat egg whites and add last.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: country green beans
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until beans are tender.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: blueberry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple; reserve juices.
Add water to juices to equal 1 cup. Add juices and water to gelatin.
Stir in blueberries and pineapple; pour in 2-quart shallow pan.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla. Spread over firm gelatin mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans and chill until ready to serve.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package; drain and add tuna, soup, milk and seasonings.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Butter or spray Pam on the interior of 2-quart casserole.
Fry sausage to brown and drain off as much fat as possible.
Grate cheese.
Beat milk and eggs
together.
Butter all bread and trim off crusts.

title: chicken paprika
directions: In oil, soften peppers and onion.
When soft add paprika, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Add chicken top with water, just covering chicken.
Simmer for 45 minutes. Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: chicken casserole with water chestnuts
directions: Toss stuffing with the melted
margarine.
Put	half of this mixture in sprayed Pyrex dish (9 x 13-inch).
Add a layer of cut up chicken.
Mix soups, sour cream and water chestnuts. Pour this mixture over layer of chicken.
Add rest of dressing on top, then add chicken broth.	Cook at
for
30	to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Mix and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool a few minutes then ice with a thin white or chocolate icing and cut in squares.
Quick cookies!

title: lemon ice box cake
directions: Combine pie filling with 2/3 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in saucepan.
Mix in 3 egg yolks.
Add remaining 2 cups water.
Cook and stir to full boil (about 5 minutes, stirring constantly). Cool about five minutes.
Add lemon juice and butter and fold into beaten egg whites.
Line spring mold pan with lady fingers (single).
Place on bottom first, then stand around sides.
Add layer of filling, layer of fingers, etc. ending with fingers on top.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
(This much can be done the day before.)
When you are ready to serve, top with whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam and drain broccoli; set aside.
Mix together cheese, egg, diced onion, soup and mushrooms.
Spread broccoli in bottom of medium baking dish.
Spread ingredients over broccoli.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers that have been mixed in melted butter. Do not pack topping.
Sprinkle it on.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until crackers are light golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: summer squash
directions: Cook squash
in a small amount of boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain.
Saute
onion
in
oleo;
add
squash, stirring to mix.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 quart casserole. Top
with
eggs,
cheese
and corn chips.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: gold water salad
directions: Let Jell-O set in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When set, add 6 sliced bananas and crushed pineapple, well drained.
Cook pineapple juice, eggs, flour and sugar until thick, then add cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Cool and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over well set Jell-O.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press evenly onto bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan (may substitute a 9-inch round 3-inch deep cake pan, greased with Crisco).
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Saute onion and pepper in butter. Remove and set aside.
Brown ground meats in skillet.
Add soup, sauces and ketchup.
Add pepper, onion and seasonings.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, gradually adding flour until dough is not sticky.
Knead 10 minutes.
Let dough rest 20 minutes; shape into a ball.
Let rise 1 hour.
Shape into rolls or bread loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and sprinkle dry Jell-O over Cool Whip and cottage cheese; mix well.

title: snicker bar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and egg; mix.
Add baking powder, soda and flour; mix well. Cut miniature Snickers in 1/2.
Wrap dough around each, forming a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cookies will flatten as they bake; with candy bar as center filling.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana orange slush
directions: Mix and freeze.
Thaw to a slush and serve.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach.
Combine with onion, soup and cheese.
Place in a greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine dressing and butter; spread on spinach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix persimmon pulp, beaten eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together, then pour into the liquid mixture.
Stir in melted butter.
Pour into the shallow pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 300° to 325°.

title: chocolate chip banana muffins(low-sugar)
directions: Combine in bowl and let stand 3 to 4 minutes the All-Bran or Fiber One and milk.
In another bowl, put the dry ingredients: flour, sugar, chocolate chips, baking powder and salt.
Add to the All-Bran and milk mixture the bananas, egg whites and oil.
Add dry ingredients to liquid ingredients and mix.
Spoon into muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: julia's open fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut butter into dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg; mix.
(If dough is too dry for spreading, add a little cold milk or orange juice.)
Spread dough on bottom and sides of 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Peel peaches; cut in slices and place over the dough (if plums are used, do not peel).
Sprinkle top of cake with brown sugar; dot with butter.
Bake until cake is golden brown on bottom and fruit is soft, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese bake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar and flour and stir in reserved juice.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Stir well.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up chicken and celery.
Put in large pan of water.
Bring to boil.
Cook until done.
Take chicken out.
Cook and debone. Set chicken aside.
Roll biscuits out.
Cut each biscuit up after rolling out.
Add one at a time to boiling broth.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Then add cut up chicken.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Mix minced peppers, sugar and vinegar in a saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil 6 minutes.
Add Certo, boil 3 minutes and remove from heat.
Stir 3 to 5 minutes and fill jelly glasses.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all but last three ingredients and put into casserole.
Then melt butter or margarine, add corn flakes and slivered almonds.
Pour over top and bake in oven 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves approximately 5 to 6.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together very well.
Press onto a large cookie sheet.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Put pineapple in large baking dish. Mix flour, sugar and cheese. Sprinkle on pineapple. Mix crackers and butter and sprinkle over top. Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients together and put in crock-pot or use microwave.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add milk to keep from thickening too much.
Serves a crowd.
Serve with nachos, bread sticks or veggies.

title: chicken elizabeth(servings:  8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt butter in large skillet and brown chicken.
Transfer to prepared dish.
Combine sour cream, Blue cheese, Lea & Perrins and garlic in bowl.
Add white pepper to taste.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve over rice or noodles. Serves 8.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Drop tomatoes into boiling water for 1 full minute.
Peel, seed and chop.
Put in large bowl with the olive oil, garlic slices, basil leaves, salt to taste and lots of red pepper flakes. Cover with Saran Wrap and let set for a couple of hours, then remove garlic.
Cook the linguini, drain and toss with cold tomato mixture, some Parmesan cheese and serve immediately.

title: banana cake and filling
directions: Bake in greased layer cake tins at 350° until done.

title: granny's old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg.
Add flour and milk.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into cakes and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: apricot nectar pound cake
directions: Mix
together
and add eggs one at a time, beating well after each
addition.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cantonese
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken.
Cut meat into thin strips.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Saute chicken in oil 1 to 2 minutes.
Add onion, green peppers, celery and 1/2 cup broth. Cover; steam for 2 minutes.
Blend remaining broth with cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Add tomatoes; cook and stir 2 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: good cookies
directions: Cream butter, honey and eggs in a separate bowl.
Blend dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Blend and add raisins, nuts etc.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Flatten cookies if necessary.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions (omitting salt). Drain well.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add broccoli and remaining ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until cheese melts, stirring often.
Serve.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: spinach and herb spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
For best results, chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put cheese out at room temperature to get soft.
Blend all ingredients except only use half of the nuts.
Roll the cheese ball in the extra chopped nuts.
Before serving, let the cheese ball sit out so it will spread smoother on crackers.

title: frypan cookies
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Beat egg with sugar and add to butter. Stir.
Add dates and cook for 5 minutes (stir).
Add nuts and 2 cups of Krispies and vanilla.
Mix well.
Chill.
Make into balls and roll in coconut.
Keep in refrigerator until serving.

title: beach broiler beans
directions: Mix all ingredients. Top with bacon. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers or in hollowed pumpernickel loaf.
Use the bread from the loaf (cut in 1-inch cubes) to dip with.

title: terrific turkey soup
directions: Boil the water. Add chopped carrots, celery and onion. Add salt, garlic powder, pepper and celery powder.
Simmer for 45 minutes (or until vegetables are tender). Add 4 cup of already cooked rice. Add turkey (watch for the bones!).
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Add salsa.
"Soup is on!"

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in medium saucepan; bring to boil. Boil about 5 minutes until syrup forms.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until mixed.
Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal. Spoon out onto greased pan or waxed paper with butter; let cool.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in order except nuts and egg whites. Beat well.	Add nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into an ungreased tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or a few minutes longer.
Let cool in pan before turning out on plate.

title: chocolate chip divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in a saucepan; cook on low heat, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook on medium heat 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan. Uncover and cook on medium heat without stirring to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites at high speed until stiff peaks form.
Pour hot sugar mixture in a thin stream over beaten eggs whites while beating at high speed until mixture holds shape.
Drop chocolate morsels to create a marbled effect.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool completely.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until sugar is dissolved, then cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze in containers to fit into punch bowl.
Take out several hours before using.
When slushy, put into punch bowl and pour 3 quarts ginger ale over it.
Makes 50 (4 ounce) servings.

title: james' company casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown beef.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and olives.
Layer in casserole dish: 1/2 noodle mixture and 1/2 meat.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rosa's christmas nut cake
directions: Chop or cut up cherries, pineapple, dates and nuts.
Crush vanilla wafers and mix with fruit and milk.
Add flavoring.
Mix well with hands.
Pour in tube pan or other.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: wine herb halibut steak
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Arrange halibut steaks in a single layer and cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Add wine and lemon juice; sprinkle basil and remaining ingredients over steaks.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve steaks with pan drippings.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on box.
Bake in oblong pan. Mix pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Pour over cooled cake. Slice bananas on top of pineapple.
Pour vanilla pudding over bananas.
Cover with whipped topping.
Top with Angel Flake coconut and pecans.

title: shrimp and crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute onions and tops in butter.
Stir in half and half.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add crabmeat and shrimp.
Cook until shrimp are pink.
Mix with prepared fettuccini.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 10-bean soup
directions: Bean mixture should contain equal amounts of the following: green split peas, yellow split peas, red beans, black-eyed peas, pinto beans, Great Northern beans, navy beans, lentils, black beans and garbanzo beans.

title: easy dill salmon cakes
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs in large mixing bowl.
Set aside remaining 1/2 cup.
In bowl, add eggs, parsley, scallions, dill, lemon juice and pepper; mix well.
Add salmon and mix with hands, breaking up pieces.
Form salmon mixture into 8 patties, 1/2-inch thick.

title: grandma's calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon.
Add onion and cook slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drain some liquid off.
Cook 40 minutes at 350° or cook in crock-pot desired time.

title: seafood cheese spread
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve on crackers (party rye and etc.).

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, walnuts and margarine together.
Pat into bottom of baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese (softened), powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Place on top of crust.
Mix pudding with milk and pour over the cream cheese mixture.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: quick country pie
directions: Melt buttah...add chips...heat til chips are melted...add remainin' ingrediments...mix 'n pore in an unbaked pie shell...bake at 350° fur 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter and press into bottom of pan.

title: beef tenderloin rib roast
directions: Mix spices together and rub generously over both sides of roast.
Place on rack in an uncovered pan and place in 450° oven for 25 minutes.
Both ends will be well done and middle will be medium.
Slice and serve with Dijon mustard or Horseradish Sauce.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix rice and soups and 1 can of water in casserole.
Top with cooked chicken.
Sprinkle seasonings.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fast salad
directions: Wash lettuce head and tear, not cut, into slices.

Place lettuce leaves in bowl; put half of peach and half of pear in bowl. Take ice cream scoop and drop two scoops cottage cheese in on lettuce leaves, pears and peaches, then place 1 or 2 cherries on top.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over ribs in a roaster. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken cheese soup
directions: Boil chicken breast until tender, reserving 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Chop carrot, celery and onion in food processor or very fine.
Saute the vegetables in 1/3 stick of margarine.
Add chicken broth and cook about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add potato soup; heat throughly and add the Velveeta cheese, which has been cut into pieces.
Simmer until cheese is melted and stir in sour cream.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Pour chicken broth into a large saucepan.
Add chopped broccoli.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Add milk, cream, cheese, ham, margarine and salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Be careful not to cook on too high a heat, nor too thin a pot.
Check seasonings, may need black pepper.
To reheat, it is best to use a double boiler.
This recipe makes 2 1/2 quarts of chowder.

title: myra's baked beans
directions: Mix beans, catsup, Karo and onion.
Pour into casserole dish. Cut
bacon into small pieces and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 275° for about 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish. Combine soup and water and pour over chicken.
Place a slice of cheese on each chicken breast.
Melt butter and combine with dressing.
Sprinkle on casserole.
Cover and cook at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
I have use shredded Cheddar cheese instead of the Swiss slices.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until done.

title: elephant ears
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water, then add 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Mix all ingredients.
Let rise about 40 minutes.
Punch down.
Refrigerate until dough is chilled.
Break off walnut size chunk.
Roll out or pull apart; flatten dough.
Melt shortening in large skillet, about 1 1/2-inches deep.
Place ear in hot grease. Brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: quick casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and cover with chow mein noodles.
Bake another 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dilled oyster crackers
directions: Combine Ranch salad dressing mix with oil and dill weed.
Pour over crackers, stir to coat.
Stir a few more times over next 30 to 60 minutes.
This stores well, but keeps best when not in an airtight container.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Cook rice and broccoli separately. Mix vegetables.
Add the soups and Cheez Whiz.
Place rice in casserole as a lining for dish.
Pour vegetable mixture over it and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes before serving.

title: dutch oven chili
directions: Bring beans to a low boil and simmer until meat mixture is ready.
In a heavy skillet, brown meat; add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil and beans. Simmer until tender.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: pastry cream shells(natas or pasteis de belem)
directions: Turn the oven on hot (500°).
Boil the milk with lemon peel. In a separate bowl mix the sugar and flour and slowly add the milk, stirring constantly.
Let the mixture cool; add the egg yolks.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Put butter in bowl and cream until soft.
Add water to melt, then add molasses, sugar and egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Drop by spoonful on well-greased cookie sheet.
May also add raisins.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake about 12 minutes.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Spread 1/2 of beans in the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Layer with 1/2 of olives, 1/2 the salsa and 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with sliced
green
onions
and	sour
cream.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: double chocolate chewy pecan brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Beat brown sugar and eggs together until light in color.
Add melted chocolate-butter mixture and stir thoroughly.
Add vanilla, then beat in flour. Stir in chocolate bits and pecan halves.

title: dream pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at low speed to moisten.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: salmon quiche appetizers
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions.
Form dough into 36 (1-inch) balls.
Place ball in mini muffin pan cup; press dough to shape tarts.
Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and eggs until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Fill tart shells with salmon mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix with egg and milk until smooth.
Must be liquid enough to flow through a funnel.
If too thick, add more milk.
If too thin, add flour.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello and water.
Add juice from fruits.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into 9-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.

title: day ahead potato salad
directions: Cut up potatoes and eggs; cover with the following:
Mix real mayonnaise with sour cream, pickle brine and all remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and celery seed to taste. (Refrigerate overnight and cover.) Serves 6.

title: ham-cheese-egg breakfast
directions: Combine bread, ham and croutons.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and mustard; set aside. Combine both cheeses with ham and croutons.
Toss.	Pour eggs and milk over all.
Sprinkle a few croutons on top.	Pour melted butter over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Last 15 minutes, remove foil.
Let stand 5 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa. Stir in milk in large saucepan. Heat to boiling. Boil until soft-ball stage. Remove from heat. Beat in butter and vanilla. Beat until thick and loses some of its gloss. Pour into buttered dish and let harden by letting it cool.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Blend all the ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: meal in one cookout
directions: Cut 30 to 36-inch length of heavy-duty foil.
Fold in half; bring up sides to make a well.
Place all of the ingredients in well.
Fold and seal edges.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes, turning package every 20 minutes.
Makes 1 individual dinner.

title: molly's banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, bananas and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients and add milk.

title: vanilla crisp
directions: Mix oleo, shortening, sugar, vanilla, eggs and soda.
Add flour.
Bake on ungreased pan at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp gumbo and rice
directions: Bring onion, green pepper and 1/4 cup water to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, garlic, rosemary, paprika and pepper to onion mixture.
Stir in another 1 1/2 cups water and both packets from rice mix.
Bring to a boil; add frozen shrimp.
Return to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes or until rice is tender and shrimp turn pink.
Ladle gumbo into 6 individual soup bowls.
Pass hot pepper sauce.
tags: quick-cooking long grain and wild rice mix

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine butter, sugar, pulp and eggs in a large mixing bowl. Dissolved baking soda in hot water.
Add to pulp mixture.
Stir well.
Alternately add flour and milk, stirring well after each addition.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients with crumbled cornbread and bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil. Chop vanilla bean; add it and vanilla to boiling sugar water. Boil 10 minutes. Add coffee. Stir. Remove from heat. Let cool. Add vodka. Pour into a gallon jug or 2 1/2 gallon jugs. Shake daily for 2 weeks, then strain through cheesecloth into bottles for storage.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients and drain.
Place in a pie tin. Top with grated cheese.
Mix eggs, Bisquick and milk.
Pour over top of meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and soup with chopped, cooked chicken.
Put in casserole dish and top with Pepperidge Farm dressing mix.
Bake at 325° until bubbly and hot, covered.
During last few minutes, remove cover and brown.

title: darlene's crock-pot dinner
directions: Wash chicken; skin and bones may be removed.
Put all in crock-pot in the order given.
Do not mix.
Turn on high for 1 hour, then turn on low for 2 to 3 hours.
Take chicken out first and put in a bowl very carefully.
Put vegetables and rice in another bowl.
Serve warm with rolls.

title: microwave bratwurst in beer
directions: Combine bratwurst and beer in a 2-quart casserole; cover. Microwave at High (100%) for 5 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium-high (70%).
Microwave 17 to 20 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Add sauerkraut; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: scotchies
directions: Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with oleo.
Melt oleo in a saucepan.
Remove from heat and add sugar and blend; add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Stir in vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts; pour into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat oysters, oyster juice and margarine and water in large pot until margarine is melted and oysters start to shrivel.
Add milk and stir.
Heat but do not allow soup to curdle.
Serve with saltines.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except rhubarb, thoroughly.
Place rhubarb in pie shell.
Pour mixture over rhubarb and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fill muffin pans about 2/3 full and bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Cool and put into Ziploc bag and freeze.
Remove 1 at a time and microwave 30 to 40 seconds. Freezes great.
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and put in baking dish.
Pour enough milk over macaroni to cover.
Add pats of butter on top.
Tear up 5 or 6 slices of cheese and stir in macaroni.
If you want cheesier, add more.
Add salt to taste. Bake at 350° until cheese begins to brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Scatter hash browns on bottom of glass cooking dish.
Sprinkle with the salt and pepper.
Mix the cream of chicken soup and sour cream together.
Pour over hash brown potatoes.
Add the grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.
The last 15 minutes, put topping on.

title: pear relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil and cook 20 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and process in a pressure cooker for 10 minutes at 5 pound pressure.

title: old-fashioned blueberry muffins
directions: Combine Bisquick brown sugar, oatmeal and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, milk and butter.
Add dry ingredients all at once; stir just until blended.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown the sugar in skillet.
Add water.
Mix other ingredients. Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: clinch mountain vinegar pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, vinegar, flour and water in double boiler and cook until thick and smooth, stirring occasionally.
Just before removing, stir in butter and lemon extract.
Pour into baked pie shell.
If desired, the pie may be topped with frosting or whipped cream.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Quick and easy, even for breakfast!
Spread English muffin with 1 tablespoon of pizza or spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cook in toaster oven until cheese melts and bubbles.

title: georgia caviar
directions: Soak peas in 2 quarts water overnight.
Drain peas and place in large saucepan.
Add enough water to cover peas.
Bring to a boil, reduce to simmer and cook 40 minutes over medium flame. Drain.
Pour Italian dressing over peas; cool.
Combine next 6 ingredients and add to peas; toss.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Serve at room temperature as a dip with tortilla chips.
Makes 7 cups.
